title: snowball
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water for 10 minutes.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Add salt, sugar and juices and cool until set.
In meantime, remove crust from cake and pull cake in small pieces.
Line mold or round bowl with wax paper. Whip one cup of cream, fold in gelatin mixture and pour layer of gelatine in mold.
Add layer of cake and alternate, ending with gelatine.
Refrigerate.
Unmold, frost with remaining cup of whipped cream; sprinkle with coconut.

title: rolls
directions: Stir 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast into 1/4 cup tepid water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put butter into warm milk and let melt.
Mix milk, butter, remaining sugar, egg and salt in large bowl.
Stir in yeast mixture and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Knead dough with as much remaining flour as needed.
Return to bowl and let rise.
Grease 12 cup muffin tins.
Punch down.
Pinch off pieces and roll into balls.
Place 2 balls in each cup.
Let rise. Bake 30 minutes.

title: drunken turkey
directions: Place turkey breast in crock-pot, skin side up.
Drizzle butter over turkey breast.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, tarragon and paprika.
Pour sherry or water into crock-pot.
Cook on high setting for 1 hour, then on low for 6 to 7 hours.
Make gravy with drippings.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease off.
Add catsup and tomato sauce; pour into casserole.
Cover with cheese slices.
Put biscuits on top of cheese.
Bake until biscuits are browned.

title: hazelnut drops
directions: Into large bowl, measure 1 tablespoon water and remaining ingredients, except egg white and hazelnuts.
With mixer at medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, scraping bowl. Refrigerate dough until easy to handle.

title: mexicalli radiatore casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Saute ground beef in large skillet, drain fat. Stir in taco seasoning, water and tomato soup.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, olives and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli baked
directions: Cook broccoli approximately 10 minutes.
Drain and add to combined ingredients:
mayonnaise, egg (beaten), mushrooms soup, cheese and onion, chopped finely.
Crumble approximately 4 slices of bread and add approximately 1/2 stick of butter to bread and spread over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 9-inch spring-form pan.
Wrap outside of pan securely with foil.
Heat chocolate with water and coffee powder in saucepan over very low heat, stirring occasionally, just until chocolate is melted.
Cool to room temperature.

title: easy pudding salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake and glaze
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar until light and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix well.
Add flour and milk a little at a time, mixing well and ending with flour. Add sour cream and extracts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients until well blended and easy to handle.
Press through a cookie press using the star tip. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: garlic-herb crusted new york strip(yield: 10 servings)
directions: Combine first five ingredients in food processor; blend until finely chopped and paste forms. Pat meat dry and rub herb paste all over roast. Cover; chill at least 3 hours. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Keep refrigerated.)

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to directions.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water.
Add sugar and nuts.
Pour batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn out on platter or tray.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: bonnie's potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except potato chips. Place in greased casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover.
Add potato chips for topping.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spray bottom of 12 x 18 pan with Pam. Pour blueberries over bottom of pan, making sure the bottom is covered completely. Sprinkle sugar over berries; sprinkle pineapple with liquid over berries and sugar. Sprinkle dry cake mix (about 1 and 1/2 box) over pineapple. Top with nuts; drizzle melted margarine over all. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. If using convection oven, bake between 300° and 325°. Juices will bubble up through cake mix. Serve hot with Cool Whip or ice cream. About 25 good size servings.

title: cheesy chicken subs
directions: Place chicken in a bowl; sprinkle with salad dressing mix. In a skillet, saute mushrooms and onion in oil for 3 minutes.
Add chicken; saute for 6 minutes, or until chicken juices run clear. Spoon mixture onto roll bottoms; top with cheese.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Replace tops. Yield:
4 servings.

title: spinach salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Clean spinach, dry and tear in to pieces.
Cut tomatoes in half; add with onion to spinach.
In a small jar, shake together everything else but oil until salt is dissolved.
Add oil; shake to combine and pour over salad.
Sprinkle with chopped, roasted peanuts.

title: seafood dip
directions: *Strain to remove excess moisture.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and lemon juice together; heat.
Put gelatin in enough water to soften.
Add gelatin to pineapple and let begin to set up.
Mix whipped cream or Cool Whip and softened cream cheese.
Fold whipped cream mixture and grated cheese into gelatin mixture and chill until firm.

title: cheez whiz or spread
directions: Melt together over low heat.
Mix well and pour into container.
This is good for church lunch.

title: green chili relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: mustard-herb dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Makes 2/3 cup of dressing.
Great on any tossed green salad.
Try over asparagus spears or green beans for change of taste.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Roll out and put on wax paper and freeze.
Take out when you get ready for some cookies.
Take a knife and cut in 1-inch pieces and put on cookie sheet.
Put in preheated oven at 350° until almost brown. Don't cook too long!

title: egg custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk, and beat well, then add the milk.
Pour into a greased and floured pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until done.
Add a dash of nutmeg on top.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice banana and place on bottom of crust.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour pudding over banana.
Place pineapple on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip Lite over pineapple.
Chill.

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat electric skillet at 350°.
Coat meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Cut into serving pieces.
Brown steak well in fat. Mix vegetables and place over meat.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken remaining sauce for gravy.

title: aunt dot's dill salad
directions: Boil veggies in water for 10 minutes. Cool. Add celery, green onions, salt, pepper, mayo, vinegar and dill weed. Chill overnight.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 17 x 12-inch or 16 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Take a meat fork and poke cake full of holes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: After slicing tomatoes, dry carefully with a paper towel. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat an egg until light and add to it a tablespoon hot water.
Dip each slice into egg mixture and then into bread crumbs.
Fry in hot margarine.
Brown on one side and carefully turn with a spatula.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: susan's pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and spices together and set aside to be used as the filling.
Mix flour, soda and salt in a bowl.
To this, add and stir until the batter is no longer lumpy, the shortening, brown sugar, molasses and egg.
Blend the rolled oats into the batter.
On a lightly floured board, roll the dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 4 dozen circles with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place half of the circles on cookie sheet.
Place 1 teaspoon filling on each of these circles.
Cover with the second half.
Seal edges.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: teriyaki
directions: Marinate beef or chicken for at least 24 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put 1 can pie filling in bottom of bowl.
Add 1/2 of pineapple, then put a layer of the cubed cake.
Over the cake, put 1/2 of the pudding.
Repeat the layers.
Add Cool Whip on top.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain
fruit
cocktail and put in bowl.
Discard juice. Dissolve dry jello in fruit cocktail.
Stir in cottage cheese. Stir in Cool Whip and refrigerate around 30 minutes.

title: sara's cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pinch off enough dough to make a ball.
Flatten a little.
Do not roll out.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes in ungreased pan until light brown around edges.
Sprinkle warm biscuits with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: frozen fruit salad(sisterhood banquet '94)
directions: Partially thaw strawberries and juices.
Combine all ingredients and freeze in 5 to 6 ounce clear cups covered with clear wrap.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.
Top with cherries.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: fruit-cheese dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the cheese, banana and nutmeg until smooth.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Serve with apple wedges, pear wedges, strawberries or other fruit dippers or cake cubes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend flour, sugar, nutmeg and butter; add egg.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Leave the margarine out overnight.
Mix butter, peanut butter and confectioners sugar together.
Place in 7 x 9-inch pan.

title: low-fat turkey manhattan
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Prepare like mashed potatoes, using only milk.
No butter!
Make gravy as directed on package.
Heat turkey up.
Put a piece of bread on plate; add a slice of turkey. Top with potatoes and then gravy.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients together and heat. Serve on buns.

title: orange fluff
directions: Crumble graham crackers in bowl.
Combine cold water and gelatin; whip until mixed.
Add hot water and orange peel.
Grate until finely chopped.
Add orange juice and artificial sweetener. Pour into bowl; chill until mixture has set 3/4 way down.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Fold in egg whites; chill.
Sprinkle crackers over top.

title: saunders mountain deer jerky
directions: Add all ingredients together and put in a quart Mason jar. Add thinly sliced deer meat; cover and let set for 12 to 18 hours. Hang dry over wood stove or oven dry (very low temperature) for 6 to 8 hours.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add flour, milk, salt, baking powder and minced onions.
Then add grated cheese to spinach.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave wine and herb stewed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken under cool running water and pat dry.
Place 1 onion wedge and 1 clove garlic inside cavity.
Cut remaining garlic cloves in half and rub on chicken skin.
Discard cut garlic.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving juices.
Heat reserved juices in saucepan. Dissolve gelatin in hot juice. Stir in cola.
Chill until partially set. Fold in cream cheese, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Spoon into rectangular dish.
Chill until set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: g h's best ice cream
directions: No eggs required.
In saucepan, heat jug milk until boiling. Remove from heat.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix until dissolved.
Add Pet milk, water and vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate for 45 minutes.
In blender at medium speed, blend fruit.
Pour chilled mixture and (fruit) into ice cream freezer.
Freeze as directed on your freezer.

title: broccoli, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in boiling unsalted water.
In a small pan, melt cheese and milk.
Put broccoli in baking dish.
Put chunks of ham on top of broccoli.
Pour cheese mixture over all. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown.

title: meaty spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges and separate into slices.	Thaw coconut.
Mix all together and place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold. Delicious!

title: chunk style applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low overnight (8 to 10 hours).
Serve warm with or without cream.

title: dian's christmas cider
directions: Better when percolator is used.
Fill percolator with cider. Put cinnamon sticks and red hots in basket.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients and chill and serve.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Combine 2 cups sugar, oil and eggs. Beat well.
Then beat in orange juice and vanilla while alternately beating in flour mixture.
Combine well.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan (batter will be thick).
Top batter with 1/2 apples and 1/2 cinnamon-sugar combination.
Pour on remaining batter with remaining apples and cinnamon-sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes. Let cool before removing from pan.

title: meatballs in buttermilk sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Shape into balls.
Fry on all sides in butter until brown.

title: grey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Spray loaf pan and mold meat mixture in pan.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour.
Pour soup over meat loaf and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water; drain.
Reserve liquid.
Melt butter; add onion and cook until soft.
Blend in flour; add broth and cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in 1 cup of drained liquid, cream, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add cauliflower.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in cheese.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch foil pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Top with canned onion rings.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix sugar with flour.
Add a little of the cold milk and egg yolks.
Heat rest of the milk until hot.
Add egg mixture and cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla last.

title: lemon refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake as desired.
Punch holes in cake with a fork when done.

title: overnight salad
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in bowl in layers as listed.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and pour on salad, covering good so you do not see things sticking up.
Sprinkle cheese on top and then bacon.
Cover with Saran Wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Combine first six ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup plus 1 tablespoon margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add raisins and 1 cup milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix. Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix. Add oats and Rice Krispies.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in a 375° oven. Cool before removing from cookie sheet. Great for dunking in coffee; thin and crisp.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over hot spaghetti noodles and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: corn relish salad
directions: Drain and mix vegetables.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil in pan; cook until melted.
Add seasonings.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate at least overnight.
Keeps 3 weeks.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreos; mix with butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 1/2 cup of crushed Oreos.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil together 3 minutes first 6 ingredients.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and set aside.
Slice apples.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Stir in dissolved cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken; top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes, uncovered, or until heated through.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with hot, cooked rice, if desired.

title: banana-blueberry pie
directions: Slice the bananas into each baked pie shell. Combine cream cheese with sugar.
Beat together well.
Add Cool Whip. Top bananas with this mixture, half in each pie.
Top this mixture with blueberry pie filling. Can be served with whipped cream. Makes 2 pies.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions; add 1 stick melted margarine and 1/2 the Eagle Brand milk.
Pour 1/2 the batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, melt 1 stick of margarine, caramels and rest of milk; mix well.
Pour over the hot cake, add the pecans.
Pour the rest of the batter over this and return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, crab, 2 tablespoons horseradish and onion.
Chill until ready to serve.
Then mix 1/2 bottle chili sauce, horseradish and lemon and pour over top.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and onion dip and spread on big platter. Brown beef and add spices, seasoning and salsa.
Cool; put mixture on top of cream cheese.
Add toppings of chopped lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Top with 2 or 3 kinds of grated cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: honey-lemon chicken
directions: Season chicken well with seasonings.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice from large lemon into bowl of honey; mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken wings until almost done (about 30 minutes). Pour honey-lemon mixtue over chicken (place slices of lemon over chicken).
Bake an additional 10 minutes or until brown.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef or turkey; drain. Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut uncooked biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole (to look similar to a Bundt cake).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into pieces.
Cook raisins or apples until slightly softened.
Mix eggs with fork and add to milk.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Bake at 325° approximately 40 minutes.

title: 7-up cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together and pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients.
Then add vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Just pour in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut-nut frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Add coconut and nuts.
Beat until thick.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Add a few drops red food color to make it pink.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Stir in 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top of crabmeat.
Place in 375° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips and set aside.
Sift the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oil, water and vanilla.
Fill 15 cupcake liners 1/3 full of chocolate batter.
Drop 1 heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture on to the top of cupcake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: devil's food float
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, milk, butter, vanilla, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of cocoa.
Pour into greased pan.
Combine brown sugar, remaining sugar, cocoa and hot water.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburg-noodle bake
directions: In large skillet, cook beef, onions and green peppers; drain fat.
Cook noodles; drain well.
Return noodles to skillet.
Stir in meat, tomato soup, cheese, chili sauce, pimiento, salt, chili powder, pepper and water; mix well.
Divide mixture between 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dishes.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles, 12 servings each.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix together milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Sprinkle crushed graham cracker crumbs in casserole dish.
Put mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg, milk and sour cream.
Add muffin mix and stir until well moistened.
Spread batter into an 8-inch greased pan.
Mix together brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over cake.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Drizzle with glaze.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Top with cherries.

title: black walnut cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until sugar dissolves and mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
In a small bowl, combine buttermilk and soda; stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to butter mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and 1 1/2 cups chopped walnuts, blending well.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until layers test done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Frost between layers and on top and sides with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped walnuts on top.

title: brussels sprouts, mushrooms and cheese sauce
directions: Steam Brussels sprouts 15 minutes.
Cook onion and mushrooms together in butter and salt for 10 minutes.
Add herbs as they cook.
Sprinkle in flour.
Stir.
Gradually drizzle in hot milk. Cook over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in Brussels sprouts, horseradish and cheese.
Spoon sauce over a dish of spaghetti and top with grated cheese and fresh pepper.
tags: lots of fresh ground black pepper

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool.
Peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in dry container.

title: fish in a vegetable patch
directions: In a small saucepan, combine tomato sauce with celery, green pepper, onion, carrot, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Spoon into a 10 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch casserole or shallow 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: shrimp creole(this recipe doubles well.)
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water and stir into sauce.
(Simmer sauce, uncovered, 45 minutes.)
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until done (5 minutes). Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix, roll and bake at 375°.
(Melt in your mouth!)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in water or broth until tender.
Add margarine to melt.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg and seasonings until moist.
Add hot water or more broth if needed. Put in casserole dish in layers of dressing, then chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or browned on top.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add milk, egg and shortening. Bake in shallow pan, skillet or muffin cups that are well-greased at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: christian cake
directions: Take 2 heaping cupfuls of patience, one heart full of love and 2 handfuls of understand and sprinkle generously with kindness. Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve to everybody you meet.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Bake in loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining 5 ingredients.
Mix together.
Shape into small balls. Roll in granulated sugar; flatten out.
Cook on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart, for 12 minutes at 375°.

title: santa fe chicken heros
directions: Pound chicken breasts slightly to flatten evenly.
Brush both sides with oil.
Combine seasonings; sprinkle on both sides of chicken.
Grill over medium-hot coals for 6 to 8 minutes; turn and grill 4 to 6 minutes more or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Top with cheese; allow to melt, about 2 minutes.
Brush rolls with butter; grill just until toasted.
Place lettuce, tomato and chicken on rolls; top with salsa or picante sauce, if desired.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf (may halve sauce ingredients).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: reuben foldovers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously at least 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on a floured board; knead 5 times.
Roll dough into a rectangle at least 12 x 18 inches.
Cut into 6 squares.
Layer corned beef over the triangle half of each square.
Mix sauerkraut, dressing and cheese; spoon over corned beef.
Fold dough over sauerkraut mixture, forming a triangle.
Press edges with a floured fork to seal.
Brush tops with butter or margarine. Sprinkle with caraway seed or poppy seed, if desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions; drain until completely dry.
Add vinegar and brown sugar with chopped peppers and onions in pan. Boil 15 minutes.
Seal in jars while hot.

title: easy peach crumble
directions: Place peaches in lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; add butter.
Cut into mixture with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over the peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crispy apple burritos
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg.
Spread each tortilla with butter.
Put heaping tablespoonful of apple mixture onto tortilla, leaving enough room for folding.
Fold ends, then roll. Place one fold in hot grease; deep fry until lightly browned. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Melt 1/2 cup of oleo; brown chicken on all sides and place chicken pieces in a covered baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine remaining oleo, sherry, soy sauce, lemon juice and ginger.
Bring to a boil; stir and pour over the chicken.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until tender.
Turn chicken once during baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix and cook cake mix as directed on box.
Punch holes in cake while hot.
Pour can of cream of coconut over top.
Combine Cool Whip, pineapple, pudding and coconut.
Beat until well blended. Spread over cooled cake.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water, scald milk, add sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat in 2 cups flour.
Add softened yeast and egg. Mix well, then add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until dough
is smooth and elastic. Place in a greased crock, cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch down, shape into rolls and let rise to double. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: cream soup
directions: Blend flour and butter until smooth; put aside.
Simmer all other ingredients until tender.
Slowly whip in flour and butter mixture until smooth.
Simmer 3 to 4 more minutes.
Strain, if desired.
Season and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add buttermilk to all ingredients and stir until you have a thick consistency. (Do not get too thin.)
Feeds approximately 15 people.

title: oriental seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add crabmeat and vegetables, cook and stir over medium-high heat for 3 minutes.
Add seasoning; stir.
Cook 1 more minute.
Serve over rice.

title: ma's zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add oil, zucchini, eggs and milk; mix until ingredients are just blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: ambrosia filled angel cake
directions: Purchase a large angel food cake or use a homemade one.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer ingredients, except Ritz crackers, in appropriate sized casserole dish, according to amount of asparagus used.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6-10 people.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half; remove pits and scoop out pulp.
Mash pulp coarsely with a fork.
Blend in lemon juice, garlic, cilantro, green chiles, tomato and jalapeno chiles to taste. Season to taste with salt.
Spoon into serving bowl and garnish with cilantro sprigs, if available.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: tomato-basil bisque
directions: Blend all in a blender. Chill. May be eaten hot or cold.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt; saute in oil.
Remove chicken; add pepper strips and saute 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Drain fat.
Mix tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and water in skillet; add chicken.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes.
Add raisins; simmer 10 minutes.
Put cooked spaghetti on platter and arrange chicken on top.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with almonds.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in pot together.
Cool, then fold in small bowl of Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust or baked pie shell.
Chill.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: busy woman's cobbler
directions: Pour fruit in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix in sugar. Slice 1/2 stick margarine over fruit. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on top. Top with thin slices of remaining stick of margarine. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: unfried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well; do not peel.
Heat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato into matchsticks.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of oil.
Combine egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add matchstick potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour the potatoes onto the prepared baking sheet; spread out.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the fries are crispy.
Turn every 6 to 8 minutes to brown evenly.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy pimento cheese
directions: Combine cheese in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add mayonnaise and garlic powder, mix well.
Stir in pimento.
Serve at room temperature.
To store, cover and chill.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together; serve with unpeeled apple slices.

title: b j u coffee cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Place in microwave on High for 14 to 16 minutes, or until tender.

title: fruity baked chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, soy sauce, salt, ginger and pepper.
Pour over chicken in shallow baking dish. Bake in preheated moderate 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Arrange fruit around chicken.
Baste with pan liquid.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place in deep frying pan.
Mix sugar, water and food coloring and pour over apples. Bring to boil and then reduce heat.
Cook until tender.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/4 of the pecans.	Form into a ball and roll into remaining pecans.
Wrap in foil and chill overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: yam and cranberry casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a 2 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir yams into cranberry mixture.
Bake until hot through, almost 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned beef stew(crockery cooking)
directions: Coat beef with flour; set excess flour aside.
In large skillet, brown meat on all sides in oil.
In crock-pot put veggies on bottom, top with beef and remaining ingredients.
Pour water over all.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.
Turn control on high (remove meat).
Use leftover flour mixed in 2 tablespoons water to thicken stew; stir in.
Return meat to pot.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: sherry's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Take out of freezer and add 1 can of 7-Up or ginger ale.
Serve slushy.

title: lo-cal graham cracker pie crust
directions: Place margarine in a 9 or 10-inch microwave-safe pie plate. Microwave for 40 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes at Medium-high (70%) or until pie crust is heated through.
Press gently with back of spoon to shape further.
Cool completely.
Fill with desired filling.

title: neiman-marcus dip
directions: Mix Cheddar, onions, nuts and bacon.
Stir in mayonnaise. Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips and margarine with sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat.
In large mixing bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Stir in chocolate mixture. Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off wax paper and cut into squares. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange drained peaches in 10-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread brown sugar over peaches. Sprinkle on cinnamon.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt; add milk and beat until smooth. Batter will be very thin.
Pour batter over peaches.
Drizzle butter over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes 30 to 40 minutes until separated.
Combine all except potato chips.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 cup nuts, then roll into a ball and roll ball into the rest of the chopped nuts. PAUL'S ONION RINGS

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in tightly covered jar.
Stir 1 tablespoon into 1 cup hot water.
Use more or less according to your taste.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Fry bacon until crisp; place on a paper towel.
Layer all these in a large bowl along with Miracle Whip and crushed up bacon and Parmesan cheese.
Place in the refrigerator for 2 hours, then toss and serve.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Mix with wooden spoon and put in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: summertime pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions and chill. Crush vanilla wafers, enough to make about 3/4 cup, and mix with about 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Press in bottom of pie pan. Stand whole vanilla wafers around the edges.
With electric mixer, whip chilled Jell-O.
Just as it begins to thicken, whip chilled evaporated milk and then combine with Jell-O.
Add pineapple, pour into pie shell and chill.

title: year round cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, pepper and pimientos; set aside.
Combine honey, oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables, mixing well.
Pack in a jar with a lid. Refrigerate for 3 days.
Good until used up entirely.

title: lisa's white grape - peach punch
directions: Combine Jell-O with boiling water and stir at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Add grape juice concentrate and white grape with peach juice.
Stir until well combined.
Pour into 2 containers and freeze until 2 hours before serving.
Remove from freezer and when it reaches "slush" stage, put into punch bowl and gently stir in 1 1/2 bottles ginger ale.
Serves about 100. (Recipe can be halved.)

title: sandy's coconut cream pie
directions: In a large glass, microwaveable bowl, stir in milk, sugar, egg yolks, and cornstarch.
Cook on high for about 9 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Filling should be thick by now.
Stir in vanilla, oleo, and coconut.
Let cool slightly, and pour into cooked pie shell.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all but popcorn and baking soda.
Dissolve over low heat. Boil 5 minutes on medium to high heat.
Take off stove and add baking soda.
Put popcorn on large cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over popcorn and stir.
Put in oven at 250° for 30 minutes and stir every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Scald the 2 cups of milk. Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla to a syrupy consistency. Add hot milk slowly to egg mixture, stirring all the time. Add drained white rice and mix well into egg mixture. Place in a casserole dish, sprinkle top with nutmeg and cinnamon. Place dish in a bigger dish and add water to a depth of 1 inch. This is called a waterbath. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: orange frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding enough orange juice to make of spreading consistency.

title: baked beans
directions: In saucepan, mix brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and coffee; simmer 5 minutes. In a 2-quart casserole, put layer of beans, sliced onion and half the mixture. Repeat. Top with bacon pieces. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bacon is cooked. Serves 8.

title: bell pepper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and seasonings.
Pour off grease.
Boil bell peppers in saucepan 2 or 3 minutes.
Cool and then slice.
In medium casserole dish, butter bottom.
Arrange bell pepper slices on bottom.
Add on top of sliced bell peppers the Minute rice, onion and ground beef.
Then add tomato sauce.
Stir a little (but not the peppers).
Top with grated cheese and bake until bubbly and hot at 350°.
Serve with green salad and slim, sliced (not buttered) French bread.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, molasses, cinnamon and ginger together. Beat well and add flour and soda, dissolved in water.
Mix well. Add beaten eggs.
Pour into greased square cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to an easy boil for 2 minutes.
Stir, stir, stir.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: baked artichoke spread
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and blend until pureed.
Put in a small ceramic baker or casserole or quiche dish. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned on top in an oven preheated to 325°.
Serve with strips of pita bread, tortilla chips or sliced French baguette.
Sliced honeydew melon or cantaloupe makes a great follow up appetizer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Crumble crackers and pour butter over crackers and stir.
Line bottom of baking dish with half the crackers; save remaining half to go on top.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish.
Heat milk to scalding. Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add corn, flour, salt, fat, onion and all seasonings.
Mix well.
Add scalding milk to corn gradually. Mix thoroughly.
Pour in dish and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large pan and boil for 40 minutes. Add onions, carrots and celery as desired. Add salt to taste. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy why not coconut cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, sugar and egg in pan.
Blend well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and 1 cup of coconut.
Cool about 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Pour into shell.
Chill at least 3 hours covered with wax paper.
Remove paper and garnish with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: sunday breakfast
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish, 9 x 9-inches. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.
Good reheated next day.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Mix
butter and add egg.
Mix clams and juice.	Mix all ingredients
together.
Fill shells and sprinkle with paprika. Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for large shells.
Cut time 5 minutes for smaller shells.

title: gladys' hot dogs in a crock-pot
directions: Cut hot dogs in thirds.
Empty jelly and catsup over hot dogs in crock-pot.
Set on High (can turn crock-pot down after hot dogs are hot).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 8 to 9-inch dish with crescent roll dough.
Brown sausage and place over the rolls.
Beat eggs with the milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Better if made a day ahead.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: wake up-shake up
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice cubes for 1 minute, then add ice cubes and mix until ice is crushed.
Use the blender to mix. When well blended, serve.

title: cheesy chicken and broccoli
directions: Oil a large casserole dish and arrange cooked, chopped broccoli.
Mix cream cheese, salt, milk and half of the Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses in blender.
Pour half over the broccoli. Layer chicken on top of broccoli and cheese sauce.
Layer onion rings and then remaining cheese sauce.
Top with remaining Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cut and peel potatoes evenly.
Dice red and green pepper. Cook potatoes until done (10 to 15 minutes).
(Do not overcook.) Drain and plunge into ice water.
Add ingredients; refrigerate. Enjoy!
Serves 6.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Skin, remove from and debone chicken.
Place in oiled baking dish.
Bake covered 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Drain fat off, if necessary.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon, onion and pepper until done.
In a large pot add all ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well and congeal in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: perky punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice, water and brown sugar into 50-cup percolator; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place filter paper in percolator basket; add cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks.
Percolate as for coffee.

title: apple butter pie
directions: Combine apple butter, eggs, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon; blend well.
Gradually stir in milk until blended.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Cover with lattice strips of crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: granny's thousand island dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise and ketchup together, then add other ingredients and chill.
Add sugar or more relish if needed.

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes. Use to baste chicken, hamburgers or steak during broiling or grilling.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: heavenly goo
directions: Make graham cracker crust 1/2-inch thick in 9 x 13-inch pan (save 1/4 cup crumbs).
Mix butter with crumbs and pack in pan. Mix pineapple, marshmallows (miniature) and cherries in bowl. Spread in pan over crust.
Stir cream and spread on top.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs lightly over top; chill overnight before serving. Serves 15.
Delicious!

title: christmas cider
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer and serve.

title: bread machine "oatmeal bread"
directions: In bread machine, place ingredients in order given.
Select "white bread" setting.
Bake according to bread machine directions.
Yields 1 large loaf that doesn't last too long! Tastes like your Grandmother used to make from scratch!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Scald milk and add to eggs, beating all the time. Combine flour and sugar and add to the mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until set.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Blend well.
Add eggs. Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
May top with Dream Whip or whipped cream.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind the tomatoes, onions, red peppers, hot peppers and celery.
Then add the pickling mixed spice, sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Cook until thick and can.
Will make about 35 pints.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 4 ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; cook for 1 hour.
Remove cover; cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: six layer mexican dip
directions: Peel,
seed
and mash avocados;
stir in garlic powder, garlic salt,
lemon
juice and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly in a 12 x
8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Carefully spread the sour cream over avocado mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush chips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion; drain. Add all other ingredients except cheese to meat mixture and stir until bubbly.
Spoon over chips.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones. Cut up and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour broth and cream of chicken soup over chicken.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together over low heat.
Add butter flavoring and nuts.
Stir together.
Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Add sugar, vanilla and flour.
Mix together.
Do not beat hard.
Stir chocolate mixture in and put in cupcake cups. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 24.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until mixture thickens slightly.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Good with hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: soup
directions: Cook beef and onions together.
Drain to remove fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, water, egg and shortening to milk. Make sure shortening is melted and sugar is dissolved.
When milk mixture is lukewarm, dissolve yeast in it.
Combine flour and salt.
Mix in milk and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Cover with a damp cloth and let set 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow cakelets
directions: Beat shortening until light.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg to blend.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Beat flour mixture alternately with milk into creamed mixture; stir in nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with marshmallow halves.
Set pan on rack until cookies are cool enough to handle.
Melt chocolate chips with butter; stir in cinnamon.
Holding cookies in hand, use a small spatula and swirl their tops with chocolate mixture to cover marshmallows; cool.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread 6 slices bread with mustard.
Top with cheese, 1 tablespoon of sauerkraut and corned beef.
Cover with remaining bread.
Spread butter on both sides of bread.
Grill on both sides until hot and cheese is melted.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini citrus bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and beat well.
Add orange juice, zucchini and beat well.
Add lemon peel and nuts.
Pour into 2 large or 3 medium-size loaf pans that have been oiled and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.
This freezes well.

title: chicken tacosmidland, texas
directions: Saute onions and chilis in oil.
Add tomato juice, paste or sauce, cream and cheese.
Add chicken and pour over fried tortilla chips to just cover chips.

title: old-fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Brown butter in pan, then add sugar and cook together, stirring constantly until sugar is melted.
Add the water; stir slowly and cook until sugar is again dissolved.
Combine cornstarch, egg yolks and milk and add to sugar mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form small balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes by hand beater).
Pour into pie pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
This pie does the impossible - it makes its own crust.

title: peanut butter muffins(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix in order given.
Mix well.
Spray muffin pans and divide evenly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Add soup, sugar, almonds and garlic powder.
Melt butter and add to crackers.
In a casserole dish, layer green bean mixture, grated cheese and crackers, then layer again.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy; drain.
Return 4 tablespoons of fat to skillet.
Add celery, onions, salt, flour, sugar, vinegar, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil to thicken.
Add crispy bacon pieces; pour over cooked potatoes.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Line a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with beef.
Pour soup over beef and place cheese over soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Mix water, egg and vinegar.
Add to dry ingredients, forming a dough.
(If you wish to freeze dough, divide dough into 5 equal portions.
Roll into 5 balls and wrap for freezing.)
This recipe makes enough pastry for five single pie crusts.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water with onion and celery.
Cook 45 minutes. Drain, skin and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli by package directions, except slightly under cook.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in a lightly buttered 2 to 3-quart casserole dish. Squeeze lemon over the top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Chop up lettuce; add diced tomatoes, diced onions and cheese.
Drain beans and add to mixture, along with hamburger.
Mix together with full bottle of dressing.
Crush corn chips to place on top of individual serving.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter in a preheated oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
In a 9-inch pie pan combine crackers, cheese, basil, oregano, salt and garlic powder.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half the mixture
into an iron skillet.
Cover with grated cheese. Add remaining
batter
over
cheese
and
bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill and toss before serving.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside in a bowl.

title: berry of a fruit pot pie
directions: Pour berries in baking dish.
Thoroughly mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over berries.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mock abalone
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
After pounding, marinate in clam juice and garlic cloves overnight. Remove, dip in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in hot oil until cooked through.

title: hot wings
directions: Stir to blend mixture.
Broil chicken wings until cooked. Place in soy sauce mixture; spoon over meat to absorb.
Return to heat to glaze.
Watch closely because soy sauce will burn quick.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine salad dressing and soy sauce in an 8-inch square dish; set aside 1/4 cup marinade.
Add chicken to dish.
Stir to coat. Cover.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: grandma's walnut chews
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour.
Add walnuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Center should be very soft.
Cut into squares and remove from pan.
Cool and store tightly covered.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Put in all other ingredients.
Mix together and then drop cookies.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dove breasts
directions: *Use salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon, garlic powder and crushed cloves to your taste

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick and add strawberry jello to hot mixture; stir until dissolved.
Fill a baked pie shell with whole fresh strawberries. Pour hot mixture over berries in pie shell and chill until set. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: best-ever spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat ribs with flour.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper.
Cut ribs into serving-size pieces; place in pan, baste ribs with sauce.
Bake ribs for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and bone chicken. Saute the onion. Add soups, chicken, chilies and half the cheese.
Cut tortillas in fourths.
Layer on bottom and sides of greased pan.
Pour mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan strips
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Cut each slice into strips.
Spread 1 side of bread strip with butter.
Place under broiler and toast lightly on both sides.
Mix other ingredients and spread on buttered side of bread.
Pour Parmesan cheese in a shallow bowl and dip each piece (spread side down) in the cheese. Freeze.
To serve, thaw slightly and broil until brown and bubbly.
Watch carefully.
Makes 130 strips.

title: layered trifle
directions: In a glass brandy snifter or fruit bowl, start with pound cake and place each layer on top of the last.
Make 2 or 3 layers of each.
End with Cool Whip and place several whole strawberries on the top.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: You will also need a 9 x 13 pan.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: corn and green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot to cook or in microwave baking dish.
Cook through until all is hot, stir.
Sprinkle paprika for color.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water and sugar 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool; mix in instant coffee and water.
Add to syrup.
Pour into 1/2 gallon bottle and add vanilla.
Add vodka.
Serve with coffee or cream.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be put in an iron skillet after greasing it with butter.

title: corn crab chowder
directions: Mix all together and heat thoroughly.

title: wassail
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: turkey breast
directions: Marinate 4 or 5 days.
Bake 20 minutes per pound at 325°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly cream honey and lard; add egg (well beaten).
Add applesauce alternately with sifted things which have been mixed with raisins and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swordfish wrapped in eggplant with peppers, cherry tomatoes and
directions: Cut eggplant lengthwise into paper-thin slices.
Cut fish into 8 even sticks, 3 to 4 inches long and 1-inch wide.
Place fine slices of eggplant overlapping slightly, on work surface.
Place one fish stick on top and wrap in eggplant.
Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon basil.
Roll very tightly. Trim edges and set aside on plate, seam side down.
Refrigerate until ready to cook.
Remove the peel from the lemon and julienne. Remove white pith and section lemon; reserve.
Bring 1 quart of water to a boil over high heat.
Add lemon peel and boil for 2 minutes; drain and rinse under cold water.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add peppers and cook, stirring often until softened.
Add zucchini and cook, stirring often until tender.
Set aside.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Wash and place into a 4-quart pot. Cover with water to within 2 inches from the top.
Add chopped onion, garlic and parsley.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Let simmer until almost done.
Add vinegar and sour cream to potatoes.
Boil very slowly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and envelope mix.
Spread on crust.
Mix cut up vegetables in bowl.
Press on crust.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap. Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Cut in small pieces.
Serve cold. Serves 24.

title: turtles
directions: Put caramels and cream in top of double boiler and stir until melted.
Add 1 pound pecans.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Let set.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Put 1 teaspoon chocolate or each caramel and pecan. Let set.

title: whole meal banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar, then add beaten eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with mashed bananas.
Pour mixture into loaf tin.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over top as desired.
Bake for approximately 1 hour. Great served warm with butter and a cup of hot English tea!!

title: butter pecan bars
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat flour, 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/3 cup margarine or butter.
Blend 2 to 3 minutes or until fine.
Pat firmly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and press lightly.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put pineapple (undrained) in saucepan; heat.
Stir in jello. Add and stir Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and pecans. Mix.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.
Cut in squares to serve. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: peanut-crunch apple pie
directions: Combine 1/4 teaspoon salt, 3/4 cup sugar, flour, vanilla and lemon juice. Toss with apples. Spoon into pie shell.
Drizzle on butter.
Blend chilled peanut butter, 1/4 cup sugar, corn flakes and 1/8 teaspoon salt with pastry blender. Sprinkle over apple layer. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick and easy fig cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box adding the four spices.
Fold in chopped nuts and fig preserves.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for about 45 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, pour sauce over cake in pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares and serve.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Yields 12 or 16.

title: cranberry spinach delight
directions: Rinse spinach and drain well. Mix all ingredients in a large salad bowl and toss with vinaigrette right before serving. Serves 6.

title: onion soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepot, heat margarine and oil.
Add sliced onions and saute over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender and transparent.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and gradually add to onions.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Bring mixture to a full boil and then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together as listed.
If you don't have bacon, you can use bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat.
Pour over baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts, then spread the remaining batter over this and bake 15 minutes.

title: barbara's pinwheels
directions: Prepare the night before.
Soften cheese, dissolve onion in 2 tablespoons water and add 1 teaspoon mustard.
Add all to cheese and blend until creamy.
Spread thin on ham slices and roll into jelly roll.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Beat in oil, eggs and plums. Fold in nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured. Glaze while cake is warm.

title: bean dish
directions: Brown ground meat, drain.
Put in baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, beans, onion, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and sugar together. Mix with meat. Put strips of bacon on top.
Cook uncovered.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Serve warm over pancakes, waffles or ice cream.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: baklava
directions: Phyllo pastry sheets may be obtained at a grocery store specializing in Greek food.
Defrost the sheets in refrigerator overnight.
Keep them covered with a damp cloth while working with them.

title: banana custard
directions: Mash bananas; add milk, sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler, stirring frequently until thick.
Pour into cooked, cooled pie crust.
Make meringue of the egg whites using 3 tablespoons extra sugar.
Bake in medium oven 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix syrups, sugar and salt thoroughly. Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in margarine, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon-baked chicken(diabetic - meat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken parts in roasting pan and brush with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Stir together parsley, basil, lemon juice, prepared mustard, remaining butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Baste chicken with mixture and bake 30 minutes more, basting occasionally. Chicken is done when thickest parts are fork-tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: orange chicken with rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Cut chicken into strips and add to oil.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Drain.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in combined mayonnaise, juice and sugar. Add rice and green pepper which has been cut into strips; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas; arrange on bottom of prepared crust.
Pour filling over bananas; cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream.
Slice remaining banana; dip in lemon juice.
Drain and garnish top of pie. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruity cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, honey and orange peel. Spread about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture over 1 tortilla. Spread 1/4 cup chopped fruit over cream mixture. Repeat with remaining tortillas, cheese mixture and chopped fruit. Garnish with grapes.

title: banana orange shake
directions: Blend all in a blender according to desired thickness.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and baking powder, then add the egg and vinegar and water mixture.
Makes 3 double crust pies or 6 single.

title: steak and vegetable casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch casserole bowl with Pam and place the meat. Prepare carrots and potatoes.
Slice and put over meat.
Then slice onion over the carrots and potatoes.
Green pepper may also be used with this dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup into bowl; add a small amount of Kitchen Bouquet and stir well.
Pour over meat dish and bake at about 250°.
Slow baking makes for more tender meat and vegetables.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar; add oil, vanilla and zucchini. Combine dry ingredients and add to above mixture, stirring well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: preacher's sunday chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Pour in casserole.
Put cheese on top, then add chips.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: green chili
directions: Can add more or less of ingredients to taste. Simmer at low heat until thick and pour over burritos.

title: graham cracker crispies
directions: Arrange graham crackers on bottom of flat 17 x 11-inch greased cookie sheet.
Cook butter and brown sugar together, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Spread over crackers. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple pudding fantasy(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix together pudding mix, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Add marshmallows to pudding mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill overnight.

title: oven baked fried chicken
directions: Crush crackers and Melba toast with rolling pin between wax paper.
Place flour on a small plate and Egg Beaters on another small plate.
Pour liquid Butter Buds or chicken broth into a large, nonstick frying pan.
Place pan on stove over medium to low heat.
Coat chicken with flour, then dip into Egg Beaters.

title: yum-yum one dish meal
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: south-of-the-border dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning mix; spoon mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread sour cream over bean mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: granny's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool
to lukewarm.
Combine milk, sugar and shortening.
Add diluted yeast, eggs and 1/2 flour.
Mix well.
Add remainder of flour slowly stirring to make a soft dough.
Refrigerate covered overnight.
Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375 degrees for 7 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: stuffed breast of veal
directions: About 3 hours before serving:
In 1 quart saucepan over high heat, heat 1 1/3 cups chicken broth to boiling;
stir in rice. Reduce
heat
to
low;
cover
and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.

title: peanut butter ripple fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove form heat. Stir in peanut butter until melted. Add marshmallow cream and vanilla. Beat until blended. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate pieces. Cut through with knife to have rippling effect. Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple pecan stuffing
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in melted margarine, cook celery and onion until tender, stirring often.
Add broth. Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing, apples and nuts; toss to mix well.
Use to stuff a 12 to 14 pound turkey.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt and the vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a slow oven (325°) about 20 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Select medium to large mushrooms.
Wash and remove steams. Cut up half the mushroom stems in fine pieces.
Take four slices white bread and prepare as for poultry stuffing (fine).
Finely chop onion and parsley.
Grate cheese.
Add poultry seasoning and salt to taste.
Mix ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add one tablespoon olive oil or melted butter.
Put stuffing between 2 mushroom caps.
Place in shallow pan; brush with butter.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pastry
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons oleo until smooth.
Add meat ingredient; mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles (use 8 rectangles for smaller squares).
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of dough.
Pull corners; twist or seal edges.
Brush with remaining 1 tablespoon of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken soup-er
directions: Bake chicken in covered pan with 2 cups water added for about an hour at 350°.
Pour soup in broth around chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour more.
If it doesn't look like there are 2 cups of broth, add a little water.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix these ingredients: eggs, pumpkin, brown sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Add cold water to make 1 cup.
In a large bowl, add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup juice and water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened. Stir in Cool Whip with a wire whisk until smooth. Refrigerate until mixture starts to set up.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into a 6-cup mold. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Unmold.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and coffee in a 3-quart saucepan. Add water and salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat immediately.
Wait 5 full minutes.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Pour into favorite bottles and chill.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water; let Jell-O slightly cool or set. Add remaining ingredients.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour 1/2 of the cake batter in bottom of pan.
Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt margarine and caramels with milk.
Pour over half-baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and walnuts on top. Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: buster bars(yields 10 servings)
directions: Mix cookies in blender with 1/2 cup of melted margarine.
Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: lite dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions, using egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
This usually takes 10 minutes less than the box says.
Spray pan with Pam before you start.
When cake is done, use a fork and poke holes all over the top.
Spoon pineapple and juice over the complete top.
Let cake cool.

title: crab salad
directions: Dice vegies in medium size pieces.
Dump into large bowl with crab.

title: vampire's blood shake
directions: Mix yogurt, vanilla, berries and 6 ice cubes in blender. Chill for 1 hour. Pour into tall glasses. Top with a big spoonful of strawberry ice cream.

title: pineapple beets
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add pineapple and bring to boil.
Stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add beets, butter and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add cheese.
Spread bread with cheese mixture and top with a slice of pepperoni and a slice of mushroom.
Spread another slice of bread with cheese mixture.
Cut in half or quarters.
Toast just long enough to soften cheese and make crusty for top of sandwich.

title: bundt cake mix
directions: Mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° in bundt or tube pan 50-60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Flatten chicken breast.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour Italian dressing on chicken just enough to cover. Marinate for 1/2 hour.
While marinating, saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms until cooked.
Cook chicken on grill or in oven until done.
Place chicken on platter.
Spread onion, green peppers and mushrooms on top of each breast.
Top with one slice of cheese each.
Place platter in 325° oven until cheese melts slightly. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream butter, salt and sugar; add eggs, 1 at at time.
Add 1 cup flour, beating after each addition.
Also add to flour, soda and baking powder.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add spices; beat.
Add prunes.
Bake in 2 pie pans, greased and floured, or greased wax paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with water.
Bring to boil twice.
Take potato masher and mash.
Beat egg and fold in.
Butter a casserole dish.
Put a layer of squash, pats of butter, cheese (grated) and then another layer with squash on top.
Cook 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Parboil the oysters in their liquor until their edges curl. Grind the vegetables very fine; add the melted butter to the vegetable paste.
Add the Worcestershire sauce.
Add the absinthe. Season with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper to taste.
Dress each parboiled oyster on a shell.
Cover each oyster with one spoonful of stuffing.
Put the oysters under the broiler until they are brown and slightly crusty.
Watch carefully not to let them burn.

title: incredible tacos
directions: Brown slightly chopped onions before adding beef to brown also.
While browning, add thyme.
To this, add taco seasoning, paprika, tomato sauce or paste, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Stir and continue cooking slowly until right consistency.
(May add water if needed.)
Fill taco shells with meat mixture.
Mix shredded lettuce and cheese in bowl.
Put on top of meat sauce filling.
Bake 5 minutes at 300 degrees.
Top with sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.

title: ruth's best vegetable soup
directions: Put everything in soup pot; bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 or 4 hours.
Just as good when leftover.

title: mexican cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients as given.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until cake is done. This is so easy to make and no shortening.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening or butter until smooth.
Add eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until bubbly.
Grease casserole with margarine.
Put a layer of corn flakes in bottom.
Add cabbage.
Pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Top with grated cheese, then put more corn flakes on top.
Bake until cabbage is tender, about 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: jackie's chili
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain. Add all ingredients except beans. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add beans and cook for 1 hour.

title: original nestle toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Heat to boiling margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Stir constantly.
Pour this mixture over the dry ingredients and beat well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add marshmallows.
Batter will be thin and marshmallows will float on top.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Check with a toothpick.
Cool for 20 minutes before frosting.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Over medium heat, cook to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, about 1 minute.
Gradually add syrup in a fine stream. Reduce speed
and add extract.
Continue whipping until mixture starts to become dry.
Add nuts and mix by hand until blended.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon.

Set aside. In a bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and salt. In another bowl, combine the egg, milk and 1/3 cup melted margarine or butter. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Lightly grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Immediately dip tops into 3 tablespoons melted margarine and the sugar-cinnamon mixture. Serve warm. Makes 12.

title: sausage mozzarella supper
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Mix with the spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, tomato juice, onion, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Grease square baking pan.
Layer half of the noodles, sliced cheese and meat sauce in pan.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle shredded cheese equally over pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: swedish pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat slowly on both sides in skillet. Stick cloves into onions.
Add onions to meat along with the carrots, celery, 1/3 cup water, corn syrup and anchovies.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Transfer meat to serving platter and keep meat warm while preparing gravy. Skim excess fat from pan juices; remove cloves.
Blend the 1/4 cup cold water with the flour; stir into juices (mash carrot if desired).
