Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve gravy with roast.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine yolks, sugar, cocoa, flour, milk and butter.
Cook over moderate heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with margarine. Bake in moderate oven until set.

title: oatburgers
directions: Cover oats and soy sauce with boiling water; cool.
Add all rest and mix well.
Form into burgers and bake, browning both sides, in 350° oven.
Serve on buns or in gravy.
Can be browned in skillet first, then put in a casserole in oven and baked with 2 cans mushroom soup, diluted with 1 to 1 1/2 cups milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until mushroom soup begins to bubble. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican pie
directions: First Layer:
Flatten crescent rolls on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake at 325° until browned.
Cool.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add next 11 ingredients.
Cook, stirring often, 10 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar and nuts together and store in airtight container.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain the spinach and dry it by pressing it against the sides of a colander with a paper towel.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls (about 1-inch).
Freeze on cookie sheets until firm, then bag for storage.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vanilla with cooked rice.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows and crushed pineapple, drained.
Whip cream and add to mixture.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and mix. Add vanilla.
You can divide dough and add chips, coconut, nuts, etc.
Form into balls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Season room temperature cream cheese with Lawry's salt, onion and Worcestershire to taste.
Spread cream cheese mixture 1/4-inch thick on round serving plate.
Top with generous layer of chili sauce.
Add layer of flaked crab.
Snip very generous layer of parsley on top.
(Do not cover with aluminum foil; cover with plastic wrap.)
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.
Truly delicious.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows and add coloring, vanilla and corn flakes.
Put on wax paper by teaspoonfuls to look like holly wreaths.
Add red hots for berries.
These are great for Christmas treats.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press rolls onto pizza pan to make crust.
Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Layer sausage and potatoes over crust.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer batter
directions: Dip fish or chicken or corn meal.

title: jenny's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
cube
eggplant; chop celery.
Cook in salted water until
tender.
Drain and put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add cubed bread.
Pour melted butter over top; add egg, cheese and enough milk to make thick soupy mixture.
Add salt, pepper, paprika
and Worcestershire.
Bake at 350° until set. Serves 4.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Jiffy mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and flatten with fork.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Cook rhubarb until mushy, remove from heat.
Add jello and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into 4 dessert cups or a small baked pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in bottom of 10x14-inch pan or baking dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on back of box; drain.
Add cheese cut into chunks and stir.
Cheese will begin to melt.
Pour into pan with butter melted in bottom.
Melt remaining stick of butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Spread evenly over top of broccoli and bake at 375° for 25-30 mins. uncovered.
(When cracker crumbs are nicely browned and cheese bubbly it should be done.)

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Mix ground apricots and coconut.
Add sweetened condensed milk and blend well.
Use teaspoons to drop small clumps into bowl of powdered sugar and roll into balls, keeping hands well covered with powdered sugar.
Cover waxed paper with powdered sugar.
Let balls stand on the sugar covered waxed paper.
Roll again as needed.
Children can do this.

title: apple mallow yam yums
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apples and yams in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows over yams and apples.
Broil until lightly browned.
6 to 8 servings.

title: angel custard cake
directions: Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars; beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Place cream cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap; shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, roll cheese ball in pecans.
Serve with graham crackers.
Yield:
1 cheese ball (about 2 cups).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender and drain off water.
Add egg, sugar, salt, pepper, butter, corn bread crumbs and sage.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 450° until brown.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Wet hands with cold water and shape into balls.
Drop into slow boiling water.
Boil slowly for 20 minutes.
Do not cover pan.

title: kid's cinnamon dough balls
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in a little bowl.
Pull pieces of dough and round into little balls.
Roll balls in butter.
Roll into sugar/cinnamon bowl.
Bake as directed on Pillsbury can.
Watch them because they don't take long.
Keep the balls small and bite size.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onion and cook in 1 stick of oleo until onions look clear.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onions and oleo with slightly beaten eggs.
Add squash, bread crumbs, salt and pepper to taste and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab spread or dip
directions: Rinse crab unless can indicates that it isn't necessary. Blend crab and cream cheese (room temperature).
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: easy cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling mix into bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of pie filling and smooth out.
Add layer of nuts.
Pour melted butter over top and smooth.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: stroganoff style casserole
directions: Press unrolled crescent rolls on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In skillet, brown beef and onion; season with paprika, salt and pepper.
Mix in mushrooms and sour cream; spread warm over rolls.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until rolls are done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground meat over medium-high heat Season meat with salt, pepper, onion and chili powder while cooking.
Drain and season with taco sauce.
Place half package of tortillas on bottom of greased pan.
Spread cooked meat over this.
Spread beans over this and add another layer of tortillas.
Cover with Ro-Tel and mushroom soup.
Place grated or sliced cheese over this.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 30 minutes at 400° if you're in a hurry.
If baked at 400°, make sure the cheese doesn't get too brown.
I've gotten a lot of compliments over this dish!
Serves about 10.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt and shortening. Mix with flour.
Let
rise
for
hour, then make into rolls. Let rise again.
Bake
until
brown.
Can be stored in airtight container in refrigerator until you need them.

title: macaroni-dried beef or ham casserole
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator at least 8 hours before baking.
Do not mix before baking!
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 1-quart casserole.
May double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: golden turkey bake
directions: Combine cornflake crumbs with melted butter.
Set aside for topping.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6 x 2-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with topping mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Put in chicken parts.
Brown on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce with mushrooms and green peppers.
Cover.
Cook until chicken is well done through, about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to rolling boil, stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, remove from heat, then add remaining ingredients and pour into a buttered dish.
Let set until firm and cool.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Put sugar and cubed bread into double boiler.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and vanilla and pour over bread.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not mix ingredients.

title: peanut butter oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa.
Add milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil in a saucepan for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls and let stand.

title: crab dish
directions: Mix together, except cheese, and refrigerate overnight.
Add cheese.
Place in 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and dry.
While still hot, peel and dice (or cube).
Boil chicken stock, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Remove and cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine vegetable oil and mustard with potato cubes.
Add stock mixture, bacon and dill and toss gently.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup with 1 cup broth from cooked chicken. (You can add the seasoning package from stuffing to soup mixture.)
Put dry stuffing over chicken and bake 25 to 30 minutes, until it bubbles.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix the water, jello and pie filling together; let set, then whip.
Mix together the Cool Whip and vanilla pudding and add to the cherry mixture.
Mix together with a Mixmaster.

title: hawaiian fish fillets
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Lay 6 strips bacon in bottom of baking pan. Slice onion and arrange over bacon.
Sprinkle with crushed bay leaf.
Place fish fillets over this. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with bread crumbs. Sprinkle lime or lemon juice over crumbs.

Lay 6 strips bacon over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until fish is done and bacon crisp. Serve with slivers of lime and a sprinkling of crushed Macadamia nuts or slivered toasted almonds. Garnish with parsley. Serves 6.

title: short bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work in flour.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Prick all over with a fork.
Cut in strips or desired shapes.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, until light brown.
Bake in an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook
spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in
margarine.
Mix
soups, Cheez Whiz, onion, pepper, chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas blackeye chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Brown meat.
Add onions and celery and cook slightly.
Add tomato puree, seasonings and the drained, soaked blackeyes with about 1 1/4 cups water.
Cook over low heat about one hour or until chili is thick and beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water, if necessary, to maintain desired consistency.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly first 4 ingredients.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls (1-inch).
Roll balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from baking sheets.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and onion in jars.
Heat remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.

title: grandmother cora's angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening to the dry ingredients.
Pour 1 package of yeast into 2 teaspoons warm water, stirring until dissolved.
Mix with buttermilk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Roll out thin and cut. Start in cold oven at 400°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, water and chili powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff mixture with fork; sprinkle with cheese. Cover; let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
A south-of-the-border sensation!

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Stir mixture into buttered pan, 13 x 9-inch.

title: sopaipillas (spanish fried biscuit puffs)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add the water, stirring with a fork (dough will be crumbly).
Turn onto lightly floured
board or surface; knead into a smooth ball.

title: snack crackers
directions: Place crackers in a large bowl, mix all other ingredients and pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°, stirring often.

title: po boys
directions: Mix hamburger and sausage meat together thoroughly.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Form into four (6 ounce) hamburger steaks.
Using long pan, put tinfoil in the bottom of pan.
Place meat into pan, spacing them out a little.
Cut up carrots, potatoes and onion.
Place all around meat.
Pour 1 glass of water in pan.
Pour tomato sauce in pan also.
Cover pan completely with tinfoil.
Put in oven at 350° and bake slowly for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: kentucky bourbon chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Beat yolks and sugar until light in color.
Beat in cornmeal and flour.
Continue to beat while adding melted butter, bourbon, cream or milk and vanilla. Pour into crust and bake until a knife comes out clean, approximately 30 minutes.
Let pie cool before eating.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Bake 1/2 the mix in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt together butter, caramels and milk.
Remove top of double boiler from heat.
Cool mixture slightly and pour over the baked 1/2 of cake.
Pour rest of batter on top of that and add nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then give it the supreme test!
Eat some!

title: mini reubens
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Split rolls in half and spread each side with mixture.
Put corned beef on roll, then top with cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: thai barbecue beef liver
directions: Will also need bamboo stick skewers.

title: cantaloupe soup
directions: Cut cantaloupe into 1 inch cubes.
Combine 1/2 of cubes plus 1/2 cup orange juice and blend in blender until smooth.
Repeat until all cubes are blended.
Combine cantaloupe mixture with remaining 3 1/2 cups orange juice and next 3 ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover and chill.
Serve in your prettiest bowls, cold. Serves 6.

title: dump punch
directions: Place ice float in punch bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and get out of the way!
Makes 40 punch cups.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon juice and extract in blender and whiz until liquid has a smooth consistency with most of coconut well blended.
Pour into saucepan and heat until thickened.
Cool slightly, then add lemon juice and extract and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell of your choice or you may pour into custard cups.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or layers.
While cake is still warm, mix milk, sugar and frozen coconut.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Pour mixture over cake.
After cake is cool, mix 1 large carton Cool Whip with 2/3 package frozen coconut, icing cake.
Use remaining 1/3 coconut to sprinkle over top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: elvis' favorite meat loaf and mushroom gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the meat, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly. Shape the meat mixture into a 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. Serve with Mushroom Gravy and mashed potatoes.

title: aunt katie's favorite apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: mom's chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Chop or put in blender the onion, pepper, celery and tomatoes.
Cook in a heavy kettle about 3 hours or until thick.
Adjust seasoning as desired.
Pour into pint jars and process in a canner.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients, then add 2 eggs and enough milk to make a thick batter.
Using small teaspoon, drop in hot grease and cook until golden brown.

title: chinese new years cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in double boiler or on low in the microwave.
Mix in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Store in covered plastic container with wax paper between layers of candy.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: orange-walnut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl combine Bisquick, walnuts, raisins, sugar, grated orange peel and caraway seed.
In small bowl, using fork, beat milk and egg to blend well; stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients just until blended.

title: fried rice almondine
directions: Put small amount of oil or butter in skillet; add almonds and cook over low heat, stirring, until browned.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Stir together and cook for 5 minutes.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Mix well and cook until well heated (approximately 10 minutes).

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until test done.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on racks.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and granulated sugar at medium speed until creamy.
Chop 8 candy bars finely, fold cream cheese mixture and chopped candy into whipped topping.
Spread icing between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Chop remaining 2 candy bars and sprinkle half of chopped bars over cake.
Press remaining chopped candy along bottom edge of cake.
Yield:
1 (3-layer) cake.

title: okra and tomatoes with ground beef
directions: Fry ground beef, onion and bell pepper with seasoning until done.
Add tomatoes, okra, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce; simmer until okra is cooked.
Serve with rice and wheat rolls.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a large pan.
Cook over medium heat until dissolved.
Boil, stirring occasionally, until soft ball. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat lightly and pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine butter and cheeses over moderate heat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Dip cubes into mixture to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli with 1/4 cup onion until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Mix grated cheese and 1/4 cup onion; add soup, mixed with 1/2 cup of milk.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Roll crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Makes six to eight servings.

title: fish and onions("if you catch it, we eat it!")
directions: Save 1 egg and 1/4 cup water, then combine cooked and drained spinach with all other ingredients, except oysters and bread crumbs.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Shape into balls (if using oysters, use small raw oysters or halve each of the large raw oysters).
Put oyster in bread crumbs and wrap oyster in spinach mixture.
Beat the saved egg and 1/4 cup water.
Dip spinach balls in egg-water, then roll once more in bread crumbs.
Yields 12 plus balls, depending on size; the smaller, the better!

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove skin and bones.
Cut chicken in pieces and place in baking dish.
Cream soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Open can of crescent rolls and spread on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: turnip and potato soup
directions: In a large pot, combine potatoes and chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add turnips and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until turnips are tender.

title: grape pie
directions: About 2 hours before baking, slip skins from grapes, reserving skins.
In a medium saucepan over high heat, bring grape pulp to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Press the pulp through a sieve into a medium bowl to remove seeds.
Add grape skins, honey, tapioca and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry.
Fill with grape mixture.
Cover with top crust. Bake 25 minutes or golden brown.
Very good.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and add to jello mixture.
Toss until coated with jello.
Press into angel food pan or oblong cake pan and chill until firm enough to slice.
Cover with Dream Whip, prepared according to package directions.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package
directions.
Pour
half the batter into greased and floured 9 x
13-inch
baking
pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt
caramels
with
evaporated milk and butter in saucepan over low
heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over baked layer.
Sprinkle with 1
cup
nuts
and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter
over
caramel
layer. Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Do not use electric mixer.
Blend well; add oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°, watching carefully until lightly browned.

title: hawaiian chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a baking pan (15 x 15-inch) with parchment paper.
Melt the sugar, butter and chocolate together. Blend in flour, eggs and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chinese chicken dinner
directions: Combine broth, cornstarch and soy sauce in a small bowl; blend and set aside.

title: dakota tradition family cookies
directions: Mix as	follows:
Pour molasses into large pan on stove and warm.
Add sugar, eggs, oleo and soda/water mixture.
Add spices and salt.
Add raisins and nuts dredged in flour.
Mix very
stiff with
flour.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut and flatten on cookie sheet with glass bottom dipped in flour.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the vegetables, soup and cheese together and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Top with bread cubes and margarine. Bake at 350° for 1
hour.

title: barbecued sauced potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange potato and onion slices in a 3/4-quart casserole dish, placing smaller pieces in the center.
Stir together water and barbecue sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave for 10 to 12 minutes on 100% power or until potatoes and onion are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Add crackers; boil 2 minutes.
Do not stir.
Pour into pie crust; dot with butter. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Put on top crust.
Punch holes in crust with fork.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jane's cucumber bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix vegetables and salt.
Soak for 3 hours, drain well.

title: tangy buffalo wings
directions: Remove	wing tips and loosen large joint
so
wings
lay flat in pan.
Broil or fry in oil until	nice
and
crisp.
(I cook mine about 45 minutes.) Drain.
Before
serving pour sauce over all.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Cook 5 hours in tightly covered pan at 275°. Do not peek while cooking in oven.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed.
Then in layers add tuna, onions and celery.
Dot top with oleo and add the milk to moisten. Cover with the bread crumbs and bake until lightly brown and crisp. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Slowly beating mixture, add well beaten egg or eggs. Sift dry ingredients. Add mix with milk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bounces back in the middle when touched.

title: spinach frittata
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package. Drain well.
Press out all liquid.
Heat in skillet the olive oil.
Saute the garlic until golden brown. Add spinach, salt, pepper and Accent.

Mix well. Spread spinach mix over bottom of skillet. Sprinkle with cheese. Cook, turning spinach, until very hot. Add eggs and keep turning spinach until eggs are cooked. Crumble and add bacon. Stir to mix. Drain off excess oil. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.

title: pull apart bacon bread
directions: Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness; brush with oil, cut into 1 inch pieces.
In a large bowl or gallon sealable bag combine bacon, cheese and remaining oil.
Mix well.
Put bread pieces in mixture and toss to coat.
Arrange pieces in a 9 X 5-inch oval greased baking dish, layering as needed.
Cover and let raise in a warm place for 30 minutes or until doubled.
Bake @ 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 5-10 minutes more.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well and form into a loaf.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with following sauce.

title: ranch beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetables supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until transparent; lima beans until not quite done.
Slice carrots and cook until slightly tender.
Drain all and toss together in large casserole.

title: emerald bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat and stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare gelatin in a large bowl according to package directions.
Place gelatin bowl on ice. Beat with beater until firm and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, garnish with strawberries.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour and Crisco together.
Add salt to taste.
Add water. Mix well.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Combine pecans (can use walnuts) sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Cut through with a knife to swirl.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Beat butter and egg at medium speed.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until well combined.
With scraper, form dough into a ball.
Wrap with wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
May keep up to 2 weeks.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Form small meatballs after combining beef, soup mix, eggs and bread crumbs.
Place uncooked meatballs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ladyfinger delight
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap.
In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, ground nuts and 2 tablespoons coffee.
In another bowl, whip the cream.
Fold 3 tablespoons of the nut mixture into it.
Cover remaining cream and refrigerate.
In a shallow dish, mix remaining coffee and Tia Maria.
Quickly dip ladyfingers in coffee and liqueur mix, then arrange a layer of them to cover the bottom of prepared loaf pan.
Spread half over ladyfingers.
Cover with layer of ladyfingers.
Spread remaining cream.
Finish with ladyfingers. Chill several hours or overnight.
Turn on plate.
Spread reserved cream over and decorate with chocolate curls.

title: easy cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Add any of the following to taste:
onion powder, garlic powder, dried parsley flakes, dried green pepper, bacon bits, sunflower seeds, dill seed, celery seed, onion flakes, chopped nuts, paprika
and red pepper.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Put beans, hamburger mixture and tomato soup in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked rum peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin peaches.
Cut them in half, remove the pit and place them cut side up in a buttered baking dish. Combine nuts, cookies, sugar and rum in a bowl.
Divide the mixture among the cavities of the peach halves.
Pour 1/3 cup water into dish and bake for about 30 minutes until peaches are tender.
Serve hot with whipped cream, if desired.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until brown; drain excess fat.
Fry onion with the bacon until it's clear.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes or until it thickens.
This recipe can be tripled and simmered overnight in crock-pot.
It makes a nice dish to take to parties or picnics.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut the margarine into the flour.
Add milk.
Stir to remove lumps.
This will be soupy.
Cook chicken and debone. Cut into chunks.
Season to taste.
Mix broth and soup.
Stir in chicken. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour the crust mixture evenly over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until crusty and brown (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: my zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in sugars, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into zucchini mixture until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool for 15 minutes in pan; remove to a wire rack.
Slice when cooled.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel slice and core apples.
Put in a 7 x 10-inch baking dish. Mix water and cinnamon.
Pour over apples.
Work remaining ingredients together to make crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Warm milk over medium heat in a small saucepan.
Put warm water in small bowl.
Stir in yeast and warm milk.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir flour and salt together in another bowl.
Stir 1 cup flour mixture into butter and sugar mixture.
Then stir in about 1/3 of the yeast mixture. Continue to alternate flour and yeast.
Beat the batter until smooth.
Cover large mixing bowl and let the batter rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Remove the cover and stir batter quickly.

title: chicken breast
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and brown in margarine.
Saute in drippings, 1 can mushrooms and 1 medium onion.
Add the following to drippings and simmer 5 minutes:
1/4 cup chicken broth and 1/4 cup white wine.
Put chicken breast in 9 x 13-inch dish; pour mixture over chicken.
Mix Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: magic finger jello
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1 cup of cold water.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, bring 1 cup water to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1/2 cup cold water. Pour into lightly greased pan and set in the refrigerator until solid (about 2 hours).
Cut into squares (or use cookie cutters). Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Place pickles, onions and salt in a kettle.
Heat sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed until all sugar is dissolved.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Freeze.

title: sticky buns(easy)
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Break 1 loaf bread into pieces, covering the bottom of the pan.
Add raisins and/or nuts, if desired.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon. Mix until dissolved.
Pour over broken pieces of bread.
Break 2nd loaf over first.
Let raise about 3 hours or until above pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take from pan immediately and turn upside down.

title: peanut butter apple bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: my sister trudy's texas cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, sour cream and eggs.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil water, margarine and cocoa.
Add hot cocoa mixture all at once to flour mixture and cream together.
Do not beat.
Pour mixture into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Place tuna in layer in casserole or loaf pan; add undiluted soup.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Recipe may be served to large groups by increasing as many times as desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: aunt clara's broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: crunchy mingle mix
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine cereal, crackers and pretzels.
Pour oil over mixture and stir until coated.
Heat in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Pour dressing in a 2-gallon storage bag.
Add cereal mixture and close securely.
Gently shake bag until cereal is evenly coated with dressing.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Rinse beans. Combine beans and water in large saucepan or Dutch oven. Cover. Heat to boil; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour or overnight. Add salt. Simmer partially covered 1 hour or until beans are tender. Drain, reserving liquid. Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces. Combine bacon, brown sugar, molasses, onion and dry mustard with beans in Dutch oven or 2-quart bean pot. Add 1 3/4 cups reserved liquid. Bake uncovered in 300° oven for 5 hours. Add additional water if necessary. Yield: 12 one-half cup servings.

title: grilled hamburger
directions: Mix sour cream, chopped green onions, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper seasoning.
Mix this in with the ground meat until combined well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Grill on hot coals and cook to desired doneness.
Mix the mayonnaise, mustard and catsup and serve on top of burgers.
Top with tomato slice, onion slice and shredded lettuce.
Yield: 4 servings. Carbohydrate 39 g, protein 28 g, fat 35 g, calories 585.

title: orange rolls
directions: Combine sugar, orange rind, raisins and margarine into mixture.
Divide dough.
Roll each half into rectangle.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Roll up from long sides.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in 2 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Drizzle while warm, with orange icing.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and fennel seed.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: smoothie
directions: In a Blender, combine yogurt, add sugar to dissolve.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside. Beat eggs well in mixing bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating well. Mix in corn oil.
Melt chocolate; add chocolate and vanilla to egg mixture.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and nuts, mixing well. Turn into greased 8-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cut into squares while warm. Yields 16 brownies.

title: boston brown bread
directions: You will need 8 empty soup cans well greased for baking the bread.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Add vanilla, salt, baking powder and flour.
Stir in bits.
Bake 15 minutes in a large, shallow, greased pan at 350°.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 7 slices bread cubed in pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over bread. Melt oleo and pour over all.
Cube 2 slices bread and put on top, pat down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beer cheese
directions: In a food processor, grate cheese finely.
Mix in garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add beer gradually until of spreading consistency.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature with crackers, party bread, or chips.
Improves with age.

title: patchwork coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, beans, cucumber, radishes, olive and salad dressing. Toss lightly.

title: easy baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp and set one aside.
Place shrimp on well buttered baking dish.
Mince set aside shrimp and saute with onion in butter.
Combine onion, bread crumbs, butter, hot water, parsley and shrimp.
Place heaping tablespoon of stuffing on top of each shrimp.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve with melted butter and lemon wedge.
Serves 2. Recipe is easily doubled.

title: cherry cream squares(a new and delectable combination of flavors.)
directions: Prepare cherry gelatin as directed on package. Chill until almost firm. Fold in bananas; pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Combine marshmallows and sour cream.
Spread on gelatin. Top with nuts. Chill.
Makes 6 servings.
Good, good.

title: chocolate fondue* * * * *
directions: Mock cream made with 1/2 pound low salt, low-fat cottage cheese and 1 1/2 tablespoons low-fat or skimmed milk.
Blend in blender until the consistency of sour cream.
For thicker cream, use less milk and for recipes calling for light cream, use more milk.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13 pan (I spray it with Pam). Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: kraut salad
directions: Toss first five ingredients.
Add sugar and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Turn upside-down and shake 3 times before serving.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle chopped avocados with lemon juice; layer over mayonnaise mixture. Cover with picante sauce.
Sprinkle with cheeses, then onions.
Top with black olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple and juice in saucepan.
Add sour cream.
Cook for 2 minutes, or until thick. Add beaten egg yolks; stir all together.
Put into cooked pie shell.
Make a meringue topping for pie.

title: chicken chimachangas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in medium saucepan and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, set aside.
Spread small amount of margarine on one side of each tortilla.
Warm buttered tortillas on heated griddle.
Place 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture on tortilla.
Add a little cheese and roll up.
Place seam side down in a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Fix each tortilla in same manner.
Heat entire dish uncovered in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with Spanish rice, refried beans and additional picante sauce.

title: lu lu paste
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar and eggs together in a frying pan. Cook on low and mix until it looks like scrambled eggs.
Chop peppers fine; chop onions fine.
When your egg mixture is done, add all of the ingredients and mix by a blender.
Use crackers, chips or veggies.
Great!

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning.
Put in baking dish.
Add beans on top, then taco sauce.
Heat at about 250° until hot.
Add cheese on top, then heat until cheese melts.

title: cheese and mushroom balls
directions: Wrap a square of cold cream cheese around a stuffed olive and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or use plain. Refrigerate.
Slice each in half before serving.

title: low sugar graham cracker pie crust and filling
directions: Mix sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Add melted butter.
Press mixture in a pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: candied nuts
directions: Coat nuts
well
with
egg
white
mixture.
Have ready pizza pan
or
cookie sheet with 1 stick melted butter.
Stir-fry nuts in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Watch closely. Store in cool, dry place.
Very good during festive season.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan in order.
Crush any cake mix lumps and be sure oleo is sprinkled over all cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In large pot, boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash well.
In small bowl with electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Gradually add cream cheese mixture to potatoes, beating until smoothly blended.
Beat in garlic salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a buttered shallow 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake covered in 400° oven until heated through (50 to 60 minutes).
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Blend cottage cheese and spinach in large bowl. Add garlic to taste. Set aside. Cook pasta according to directions on box. Stuff shells with cheese mixture. Put in baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce. Microwave until hot.

title: president eisenhower's sugar cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly and cream until fluffy.
Stir in unbeaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with cream. Chill for one hour; roll and cut in any desired shape.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pavlova
directions: Cooking time:
1 1/2 hours.
Temperature:
You will need a pizza pan or cookie sheet.

title: aunt bill's candy
directions: Melt
cup
of
sugar in a heavy skillet until brown. Bring to	a boil the 2 cups of sugar, half and half, then add the browned
sugar
mixture.
Stir
constantly	while bringing this mixture to a
soft	ball.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir vigorously for
about 5 minutes.
Add butter and let cool for about 10
minutes.	Add
nuts
and vanilla.
Beat and pour into a buttered pan
x 8-inch).
When cool, cut into small squares.

title: sourdough steak(chuckwagon grub)
directions: Using meat tenderizing mallet, pound steak to one-half inch thick.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Combine flour and seasonings.
Dip pounded steak in sourdough starter, then in flour mixture.
Fry in 1 inch of hot lard in heavy skillet.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill overnight before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: oven macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Cook, covered, for ten minutes or until macaroni is just about tender, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes, to finish cooking.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: jug pickles
directions: Wash and slice onions and cucumbers.
Mix remaining ingredients to make syrup.
Put onions and cucumbers in jug and pour syrup over top.
Mix well and put in refrigerator.
Next day, take out of refrigerator and shake well.
Repeat this for 6 days.
On the 7th day, they may be eaten.
Pickles must be refrigerated.

title: lamb stew
directions: Brown lamb and add water, bay leaves, thyme, garlic, pepper, carrots, onions, potatoes, and wine or beef broth.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Six 1 1/4 cup servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for a few hours or overnight.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine cocoa, flour and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add sauce and soup.
Cook on low heat until thickens.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: In a medium-size heavy saucepan, bring 3 cups water to a boil. Add garlic, potatoes and bay leaf.
Cook, partially covered, over moderate heat until potatoes are "fork tender" (reserving 3 tablespoons cooking water).
Discard bay leaf, transfer potatoes to a large mixing bowl.
Add margarine, buttermilk and yogurt.
Beat with a mixer, then add just enough of the reserved water to make the potatoes creamy.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water just to cover until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add milk, reserving 1/2 cup.
Shake flour and 1/2 cup milk in covered jar to blend.
Very gradually add this to the vegetables in the milk.
Stir well to thicken slightly. Add shrimp.
Cook over low heat until very warm, but do not boil. Add butter; sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Serve with saltines or oyster crackers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs with wire whisk.
Add margarine, syrup, sugar, brown sugar, salt, flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick mix and milk until soft dough forms.
If dough is too sticky, gradually mix in enough baking mix to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with mix.
Roll dough into rectangle shape 1/4 inch thick.
Spread sausage and cheese over entire surface.
Roll dough in a log, wrap in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut log into 1/2 inch thick pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes (until golden brown).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add to mixture part of the flour, then milk until mixed well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: ribs
directions: Bring ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, water, chili powder and Tabasco to a boil.
Place sliced lemon and onion on top of ribs. Cook ribs at 450° until brown.
Add sauce and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish. Brown milk and onion. Add rest of ingredients and pour over rice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail party wieners
directions: Cook all ingredients in saucepan on medium heat 15 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together and form into a ball.
Chop walnuts, enough to cover ball, and roll ball in nuts.
Just before serving, pour caramel sundae topping over cream cheese ball which is placed in center of a platter.
Slice different colored skin apples into thin quarters around platter and dip into ball.
Light cream cheese, brown sugar and topping may be substituted.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the Bisquick, cheese and pepper. Stir in beaten eggs just until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt margarine over medium heat. Using about 2 tablespoons of mixture for each round, cook 4 rounds at a time about 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until brown.
Keep warm while cooking remaining rounds.
Makes about 12 rounds.

title: grilled pineapple chicken
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.

In a shallow pan, combine garlic Dijon flavor with pineapple juice, soy sauce and brown sugar. Place chicken in this mixture; pierce deeply with a fork and marinate for 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken to grill or broil for about 5 minutes per side or until thoroughly cooked.
Baste occasionally with remaining marinade.
Serve with sliced orange.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the bag of Oreos; press half of the Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In one bowl, beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
In another bowl, beat the vanilla, instant pudding and milk.
Fold together both bowls and spread over the layer of Oreos; place the remaining Oreos on top.
Chill 12 hours or overnight.

title: best yet onion rings
directions: Mix together and let rest for 3 hours and then coat 1/4-inch slices of onion and deep fry; drain.
Mix must set up for 3 hours.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the eggs, sugars and shortening.
Add the vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour, oats, salt, baking soda and powder.
Combine the ingredients into a dough. Mix in the chocolate chunks and pecans.
Roll into 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: homemade noodles
directions: When making homemade noodles, always use 2 tablespoons of milk and 2 pinches of salt for each egg used.

title: oatmeal softies
directions: Mix ingredients making a sticky dough.
Spoon (using tablespoon) onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cookies should be slightly brown.
Let cool on pan before removing them with spatula.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add nuts and chocolate chips as desired.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Place a Rolo on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt
margarine
in
12-inch Dutch oven.
Beat together ingredients and pour into oven.
Bake covered with 16 coals on top and 14
coals on the bottom, 25 to 30 minutes, until puffy and light brown.

title: tacos
directions: First you need sticking spray on the pan so it won't stick. Then you make the dough into a flat circle.
Put some cheese on and then sauce and then pepperonis.
The sauce is sauce is spaghetti sauce.
Cook it for 15 minutes at 100°.
That's how my mommy makes my pizza for lunch.

title: turkey skillet supper
directions: Brown turkey meat; add soup and simmer gently for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle	with almonds.
Spoon over mashed potatoes or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: In a saucepan, make a syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon candies and food coloring.
Cook apples in the syrup until tender. Chill apples and serve as a salad or a meat garnish.
Reserve syrup and serve on pancakes, waffles and French toast.

title: caesar mayonnaise dressing
directions: Whisk in a blender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.
Keeps in a jar in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: easy coleslaw(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well and set aside.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Blend in flavorings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Have potatoes ready.
Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Heat until bubbly.
Add onions and milk and cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Fry 2 pieces of bacon to get the fat and use 3 pieces of sliced cheese.
Place 1/2 of the potatoes in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle a little extra salt over the potatoes, then put 1/2 of the sauce over the potatoes and some of the bacon fat and 1 piece of cheese.
Tear cheese into small pieces over top, then put the rest of the potatoes, sauce and bacon fat and 2 pieces of cheese on top.
Cover the dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Add meat, spices, onions and rice and mix well with hands. Core cabbage.
Place in large pan of salted water.
Scald cabbage and separate leaves.
Cut vein and discard.
Roll meat in cabbage leaf and tuck inside. Place on a layer of extra cabbage. Brown bacon and mix with soup. Pour over stuffed cabbage.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole.

title: beef stew(electric skillet)
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°. Combine flour, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Dredge meat in flour mixture. Add fat to skillet. Melt. Brown meat (1 pound at a time). When all meat is browned, add enough water to barely cover meat (2 to 2 1/2 cups). Bring to a boil at 300°; turn temperature down to medium and simmer. Cover; close vent. Cook 45 to 55 minutes, until meat is almost tender. Check water level periodically; if low, add a little water. Stir occasionally. Add vegetables and seasonings. Turn temperature to 300° until boiling, then reduce to medium. Simmer and cook until vegetables are tender (30 minutes). Add water if needed to barely cover vegetables. Thicken liquid with flour and water, stirring to form a smooth paste. Season to taste.

title: cheese triangles
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, until spreadable.
Spread on frozen bread slices 1/4-inch thick.
Trim crusts off.
Cut in fourths (triangles).
Freeze, unbaked, on cookie sheet.
Once frozen, can bag in a Ziploc bag.
Bake later.
Spread out frozen on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes (until light and crispy).

title: pork loin parmigiana
directions: Remove bone and fat from pork loin chops; save all small pieces of meat.
Heat oil in deep skillet or Dutch oven hot enough so that a water drop dances.
Beat eggs in 1 small bowl.
Pour bread crumbs in another.
Dip pork loin chops in egg, coat throughly in bread crumbs, then fry until brown in oil.
Drain breaded chops on paper towel.
Arrange all fried pork in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Cover with cheese slices.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top to cover.
Then microwave on High for 5 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream together the first 3 ingredients and gradually add the remaining ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Turn oven up to 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before removing.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mash bananas with a fork.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, until golden brown and splits slightly.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and onions and drain.
Combine all ingredients, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
In saucepan, bring butter, shortening, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake in cake pans (greased and floured) for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Fill blender with all ingredients and finish filling with ice.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and water to boil.
Beat 2 eggs and stir into mixture while cooking.
If not thick enough, add some cornstarch.
Mix cornstarch with cold water.
You may try some sweet pickle solution if you wish.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Place margarine in a 2-quart rectangular dish and microwave on High 40 seconds.
Stir in honey, mustard, curry powder and salt. Roll chicken pieces in mixture and arrange in a single layer, with meat portions to the outside of the dish and the bony pieces in the center.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 9 minutes. Turn each pieces over, baste with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Re-cover and microwave on High 9 to 11 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings, and it is good served over curried rice.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Saute meat and onion until meat loses its pink color; drain. Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni.
Simmer on low heat about 1 hour.
Add macaroni and 1 cup of water, if needed. Continue simmering until macaroni is done.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
You may use leftover pot roast and broth in place of hamburger and add any leftover vegetables you might have in refrigerator.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on each.
Roll up and chill 2 hours.
Slice into 1-inch slices.
Serve plain or dip in salsa.

title: frozen pudding-wiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in a bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 12 of the crackers.
Top with remaining crackers, pressing lightly and smoothing around edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in 2 cups water for about 15 minutes (covered).
Combine the broccoli, soups, milk, Cheez Whiz and chopped onion.
Mix in rice.
Put in covered 2-quart dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: pound cake *
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Pour in dry ingredients, alternating with milk and flavoring.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Cut the oleo into the flour.
Add the nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: To chopped apples, add cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/3 cup sugar; add orange rind.
Let stand.

title: brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat about 3 minutes with mixer and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Bake in greased sheet cake pan.

title: best baked cheese cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes (leave oven on).
At medium speed mix sour cream, 3/4 cup sugar and almond extract.
Pour over cake.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Delicious eaten plain or topped with your favorite pie filling.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in large bowl and set aside.
Put oil, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the chopped pecans.
Spread in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: fun frozen bars
directions: Prepare juice according to directions.
Pour into Dixie cups. Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Insert popsicle sticks; freeze. Remove cup from frozen bar.
Enjoy!

title: carrots
directions: Combine drained carrots with mixture of next 5 ingredients. Put in casserole. Top with crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix together and add enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove top and seeds from green peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes, drain.
Brown onion and meat in fat, drain.
Add tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Stuff peppers and top with buttered crumbs. Stand upright in greased baking dish.
Add tomato soup to dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spiced peanuts
directions: Boil sugar, water and spices until syrup spins a thread as it drops from a spoon.
Add peanuts to syrup.
Stir until nuts look dry.
Pour onto waxed paper and let stand until cold and dry.

title: reuben spread
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. slow cooker combine the first five ingredients. Cover and cook for two hours or until cheeses are melted.
Stir to blend.
Serve warm with rye bread or crackers.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Heat the over to 400 F. Pierce the potatoes in several places with a fork.
Place on a baking sheet or oven rack.
Bake for 50-60 minutes, or until the potatoes feel soft when squeezed. Remove the potatoes from the oven and let cook for 15 minutes.

title: chuck wagon surprise
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in saucepan, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add macaroni, spaghetti sauce and cheese; mix well.
Simmer until heated through.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Blend all dry ingredients; add shortening and blend.
Add milk slowly.
Blend in egg.
Stir until stiff dough is blended.
Put on floured board and knead 5 times.
Cut and bake.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook until onions are clear.
Add soup, tomatoes and chilies and beans.
Warm through.
Top with cheese and olives.
Serve hot with tortilla or nacho chips.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Put 1/2 cup flour aside and mixing raisins and nuts together with flour, mix with batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: 5-pound chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream and butter. Bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir marshmallow cream and chocolate chips into boiled mixture until chocolate is melted. Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares. Makes 5 pounds.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Beat together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, bananas, sour cream or buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: "corn pudding"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add 8 ounces sour cream. Mix well.
Add corn muffin mix.
Mix together well.
Drain whole kernel corn; add to sour cream/corn muffin mixture.
Mix well.
Add can creamed corn.
Mix well.
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until turns lightly brown.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese starts to melt.
Enjoy!

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix together in pan.
Heat over low heat until ready to serve. Remove cinnamon sticks.
Serves 8.

title: creole-style green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add tomatoes.
Cook constantly until thickened.
Add beans; heat.
Top with bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute meat, onions and celery.
Add tomatoes, Au jus gravy, and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and cabbage.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add macaroni and parsley and cook 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread rice over butter.
Sprinkle on soup mix.
Pour on water.
Arrange chicken on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Mix together the Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice and let stand for five minutes.
Then add the pineapple, drained, and the Cool Whip and nuts.

title: moist german chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Melt in saucepan: Baker's chocolate, butter, hot water and vanilla.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup dry mix, then combine all of the ingredients together.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch pans for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost as desired. Cool Whip works well on this cake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the flour, shortening and milk; stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or cloth; knead just until smooth. Roll dough out into large rectangle, 1/4-inch thick.
Spread peaches on dough; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Seal edges with a little water.
Cut into 12 to 15 pieces; place in pan with butter.
Boil sugar and water until melted; pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until golden brown, not dry.

title: basic roll dough
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar and shortening; add salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry mixture; add egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make soft dough.
Shape into ball. Place in lightly greased bowl, turn once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down, turn out on floured surface.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes. Shape into desired rolls.
Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake on greased baking sheets or in greased muffin pans in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen rolls.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and set aside.
Melt margarine in bottom of pan. Layer with potatoes, carrots, onions, celery and peas.
Salt and pepper as you go. Cover with hamburger and meat.
Mix pea juice and tomato soup; pour over meat.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in slightly greased casserole dish or pan.
Mix dry ingredients until mealy.
By hand, sprinkle over fruit.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine or butter and pour over the crust mix.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, put the chopped meat, chopped onion and pepper.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the water and mix. Add to chopped meat, onion and pepper mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: surprise chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in salted water and cut into small pieces.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chilies and seasonings.
Steam tortillas until soft.
Fill a soft tortilla with 1 tablespoon chicken, 1 tablespoon onion and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll.
Fill flat casserole dish.
Pour Ro-Tel mixture over this.
Sprinkle more onions and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: szechuan green beans(microwave)
directions: Place garlic, ginger and scallions in the work bowl of a food processor.
Process until finely chopped.
Remove to a 14 x 11 x 2-inch dish. Add oil and pepper flakes. Cook uncovered at 100% for 3 minutes.

title: hawaiian beef dinner
directions: In Dutch oven or heavy kettle, brown beef in fat.
Add onion, salt, garlic and ginger. Drain pineapple and reserve syrup. Add enough water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups. Add 1/2 cup to meat and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Slice green pepper and water chestnuts.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl and mix gently. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Drain before serving.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and milk gradually.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat, then add beaten eggs.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: ho-bo stew
directions: Layer the ingredients in
order
in
large baking dish. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: egg casserole
directions: Spread croutons or hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased). Put on top cheese (1 1/2 cups; reserve 1/2 cup for top) and then browned meat.
Beat eggs; add milk and dry mustard.
Pour over meat; put in fridge overnight.
Then put soup, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Freeze or bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: round steak skillet meal
directions: Cut steak into 6 serving size pieces. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Pound flour mixture into the steak. Brown in hot oil. Add bouillon cube, water, celery, onion and carrots.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until steak is tender. Add small amounts of water as needed.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and peas to the meat mixture. Simmer for 10 more minutes. Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place lettuce on bottom of bowl.
Mix next 6 ingredients; place on lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and then the cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Top with Bac*Os or crisp bacon bits.

title: honey berry milk shakes
directions: In a blender, combine the ice cream, berries, milk and honey; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into glasses.

title: rice krispie candy
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat, add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir peanut butter into marshmallows.
Add Rice Krispies, stir until well coated.
Press into buttered dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar, vanilla and buttermilk; stir. Add eggs and stir. Then add coconut and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until dark golden brown. Remove and cool.

title: home-style meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, breadcrumbs, onion, salt, pepper, milk, parsley, catsup, mustard, Worcestershire and eggs in large bowl.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Meat loaf may be baked in the pan or, if preferred, turned out onto greased baking dish.
If baking unmolded, cover meat with several strips of bacon.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into pieces.
Mix together chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice, almonds and salt.
Top with Parmesan cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until hot.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Then stir in pineapple, eggs and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fuzzy cookies
directions: Cook sugar, dates, egg and butter over medium heat, in heavy pan, until blended and thickened.
Cool well and add vanilla.
Add cereals, nuts and coconuts to the cooked mixture.
Shape into balls; roll in additional coconut.
Note:
I made these diabetic by eliminating the sugar in the dates and using sugar-free coconut.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Press in beef mixture.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix first three ingredients well.
Stir in next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: malibu layered salad
directions: Add ingredients in layers.
Put lettuce, onions, peas and mayonnaise, with sugar mixed in, into a 13 x 9-inch glass cake dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, sprinkle cheese, eggs and bacon on top of salad.
Garnish with tomatoes and/or grated cheese, if desired.
Serve slightly chilled.

title: easy crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and celery in butter or oleo.
Add garlic, parsley and crawfish or shrimp to mixture and cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, half and half and cheese to mixture.
Taste for salt.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: easy mayonnaise cake
directions: In mixer bowl, blend all ingredients on low; beat about 2 minutes until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan (fill pan a little over 1/2 full).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: tamale dip
directions: Melt Velveeta; add tamales, chili and Tabasco to taste.
Mix well.
Heat through and serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice in sauce pan until bubbly.
Add jello, remove from heat.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Let cool slightly.
Pour into 8 by 8 inch pyrex dish.
Stir in cool whip, buttermilk, and pecans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: easy candy (good for kids)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and form into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and place on wax paper to harden.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix and let rest in refrigerator 1 hour before using. This recipe enough for 1 pound shrimp or a large onion for onion rings.

title: cheesy squash puppies
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain well.
Mash and drain again. Combine eggs and squash; mix well.
Combine corn meal, flour, onion and cheese in a bowl.
Toss to mix.

title: amish bread and friendship loaf cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into two well-greased and sugared 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
The dough may also be used in 5 mini-loaf pans.
Then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ritz cracker delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers, in microwave bowl.
Cook in microwave until mixture is thick and spreadable like peanut butter.
Spread on crackers; place on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put small amount of cream cheese frosting on top.

title: dirt cake
directions: You also need 1 clean, new flowerpot.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Slice cabbage and onion and cover with sugar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and let stand 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Will keep 7 days.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and applesauce.	Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in
zucchini.
Bake
at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 4 mini loaf pans.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip eggplant slices in milk and egg and fry in olive oil. Layer this alternately with sauce and ground beef.
Top with a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese, then Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream together margarine/butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add in eggs, flour, baking powder, milk, lemon extract, vanilla and walnut extract.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix 1 teaspoon flour with black walnuts so they don't sink to the bottom.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Take head of lettuce and tear (not cut) into small bite size pieces.
Put in bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix with hands first to moisten everything, then use plastic spoon to finish.
If not enough mayo, you can add 1/2 cup more.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir together flour and baking soda.
Add to batter. Mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: banana-walnut bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat sugar and shortening just until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except walnuts. Beat until well mixed.
Increase speed to high and beat 2 minutes. Stir in walnuts.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool cake 10 minutes in pan. Remove to wire rack.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, vanilla pudding and oil well.
Add Seven-Up and beat well.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: plantation clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter in a microwave bowl; melt for 3 minutes on 50% power.
Stir remaining ingredients together with melted almond bark.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients into small balls.
In large pan, combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Mix well and simmer.

title: microwave cracker jacks
directions: Put brown sugar, white syrup, butter and salt in bowl and boil in microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well.
Spray a brown paper bag well with Pam.
Put 1 gallon popped corn in bag.
Pour in syrup mixture.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake well.
Put in for another 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake well.
Put back in for 1/2 minute on High.
Take out, shake well and put on cookie sheet to cool.

title: jan's chicken and dumplings
directions: Spread very, very well before making the balls which should not exceed 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Broil.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Tear the angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: french beans
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add catsup and drained French beans.
Toss and heat over low heat.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar then eggs.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well. Then add sweet milk and mix well.
Preheat oven to 250 degrees. Put in deep dish pie crust and pick with fork for 5-10 minutes until it quits popping.
Pour in filling an bake for 4 minutes. Turn oven to 300 degrees an bake for 1 hour or until pie is set.

title: jello pie
directions: Pour 2 small boxes jello in glass bowl.
Add just enough water to stir (not much or pie will not set up).
Add Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer ingredients as they are listed in 8 x 12-inch baking pan. Smooth can of cherry pie filling in pan.
Smooth pineapple and juice next.
Sprinkle sugar over pineapple.
Shake dry cake mix on top.
