Pour melted margarine and smooth over top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done.
Drain and cool to room temperature.
Mix taco seasoning, tomatoes, beans and cheese. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Add ground beef, taco sauce and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add lettuce and Doritos.

title: baked chicken and broccoli for two
directions: Place chicken in 9 inch square pan, and drizzle with butter. bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Arrange around chicken. Combine soup, milk, and cheese; pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika. Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into batter.
Add blueberries mixed with 1 tablespoon flour.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peoria rhubarb cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
In large mixing bowl, stir together the sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs and blend well.
Gently stir in rhubarb.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
In small bowl, stir together 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in 1/3 cup margarine.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Cover edge of pie with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Remove foil and reduce heat to 375° and bake for another 25 minutes or until topping is golden.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Cover
bottom
of
12-inch
Dutch
oven
with
open and flattened chilies.	Sprinkle cheese evenly over chilies.
In a separate
bowl
mix
eggs,	evaporated
milk
and flour.
Pour mixture over
cheese and chilies.
Bake for 40 minutes with 12 coals on
top
and 9 coals on bottom.
After baking, cover top with Jack
cheese and pour tomato sauce over cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes more with 12 coals on top and 6 coals on bottom.

title: tangy sauerkraut relish
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss until well mixed. Chill in covered container overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 6 tablespoons margarine.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes and let cool.
Cream 1/2 cup margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at high speed until fluffy.
Spread on crumb crust.
Place sliced bananas on top of filling.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Whip the topping and spread over fruit. Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter bread sticks
directions: Trim off bread crust and cut each slice in four pieces (sticks).
Combine peanut butter and cooking oil.
Toast bread sticks in 250° oven until crisp, about 30 minutes.
Dip each piece of toasted bread in peanut butter mixture and then roll in cracker crumbs.
Lay out on cookie sheet for at least 12 hours.
These may be frozen.

title: golden chicken and orange sauce
directions: Remove any excess fat and excess skin from chicken parts. Rinse under cold water.
Pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper. Heat butter and oil in a large, heavy skillet until hot.
Brown chicken pieces, a few at a time, starting with skin side.
Brown quickly and remove to a plate.

title: okra-bacon casserole
directions: Slice okra into thin rounds.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Place layers of okra, tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Season each layer with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Lay bacon overlapping on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Combine with other ingredients and pour into greased 9-inch casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Cook on low heat.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk; stir well.
Add cheese, a small amount at a time.
Stir constantly.

title: crab dip
directions: Saute
onions and butter until clear.
Add cream cheese and melt over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add crabmeat and hot sauce;
blend well.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, Veg-All, soup, onion, pepper, sour cream and cheese together.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top. Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix together soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 the can of fried onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: light cheese ball
directions: Soften Swiss cheese and cream cheese.
Blend all ingredients in a food processor until well mixed.
Form into a ball and chill in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours, then roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: cheese balls
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green peppers, onion and salt.
Shape into balls and roll in the remaining pecans.
Chill.

title: heart smart tortilla chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each tortilla into 6 wedges and sprinkle with seasonings; toast 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp. Yields 6 ounces.

title: cherry creme pie
directions: Pour pie filling into crust, reserving a couple spoonfuls for top.
Mix milk, instant vanilla pudding and Dream Whip.
Beat together until thick.
Spread over cherries.
Decorate with reserved cherry filling.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Pour 1/2 batter in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool. Pour milk into a saucepan, add butter and heat slowly. Add caramels. Stir mixture so that caramels melt and all ingredients are combined. After liquid ingredients are combined, remove from heat and let cool slightly. Pour mixture over cooked cake. Sprinkle morsels and pecans on top of mixture. Pour/spread remaining cake batter on top. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until batter is done. Serve with ice cream.

title: swiss crisps
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon of the bread crumbs in a small bowl. Place remaining bread crumbs in a pie plate.
Dip cheese cubes into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs to coat well.
Melt enough shortening or pour in vegetable oil to make a 3-inch depth in large saucepan or electric fryer; heat to 380°.

title: caesar pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Add broccoli, cauliflower, cucumber, tomato and red pepper.
Toss salad with Caesar salad dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Chill.
To serve, squeeze lemon juice over salad; garnish with fresh parsley. Serves 4 to 6.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
If frosting is too stiff, add a little more water.
This will ice a 3-layered cake.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Bake another 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Let cool.
Cook rice. Drain asparagus and put on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and onion soup.
Add rice (already cooked) and then add deboned chicken.
Pour mixture over asparagus and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add all the dry ingredients until mixed together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut each into 1/8-inch wedges.
Place wedges, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Brush potatoes with half of oil mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally with remaining oil mixture.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine cooked chicken, oranges, pineapple, celery and grapes with the mayonnaise and mustard.
Serve on lettuce leaf and top with chow mein noodles.
It is also good served with cantaloupe ring.

title: custard corn
directions: Pour melted butter into scalded milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set dish in water.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to apple mixture.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Double for 12 people.
Serve with ice cream or plain.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and butter.
Cook in an iron skillet until thick.
Add vanilla.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Cut eggs longways.
Take the yellow out of the egg.
Smash this with a fork in a mixing bowl.
Add relish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
(Add more mayonnaise if you want them creamier.)

title: fantasy fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth and chill.
If too thick, add milk a little at a time.
Serve with any fresh fruit, i.e., strawberries.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Blend in sugar.
Add milk, flavoring and coconut.
Pour into pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parkerhouse rolls
directions: Mix together boiling water, sugar, shortening, and salt. Cool; set aside.
Beat eggs.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water; cool.

title: marble squares
directions: Beat until creamy the butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Sift, while mixing in, the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Bake at 375° for 1 minute to melt chocolate morsels.
Run knife through dough to marbleize. Bake 12 to 14 minutes more.
Makes 24 squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add milk, salt, flour and peppers.
Mix with corn.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch pan lined with waxed paper. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: mom's chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, walnuts, vanilla and 3 egg yolks in a bowl and beat with electric mixer until well blended. Melt semi-sweet chocolate in double boiler over medium heat and combine with other mixture in bowl.
Continue mixing and fold in 1 cup whipping cream and egg whites.
Fill in graham cracker crust, cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: best in the west beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Fry bacon and saute onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together the shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla. Add rest.
Can add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mushroom  soup
directions: Dice carrots and potatoes; boil until tender.
Saute onions; add fresh mushrooms.
In large pot, mix the cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups and straw mushrooms.
Add the carrots and potatoes with water they were boiled in.
Simmer for a few minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in stuffing mix.
Line a baking dish with half of the stuffing mixture.
Combine all remaining ingredients and spoon over stuffing mixture.
Cover with the remaining stuffing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; add salt and spaghetti sauce.
Unroll and separate dough into triangles.
Place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan, pressing together to form a crust.
Turn mixture into unbaked crust and top with cheese slices.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate whip pie
directions: Prepare 8-inch baked graham cracker crust.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cabbage in wine
directions: Cook onion and cabbage in hot olive oil about 10 minutes.
Add fennel seed, tomato, salt and sugar.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Pour in wine and lemon juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Grease casserole or roaster with butter.
Dredge chicken with flour as for frying.
Put chicken with skin side down in roaster. Salt and add water and butter.
Put into 450° oven and brown. When brown, remove from oven and turn.
Brown this side and if all water has cooked out.
Add a little more.
When brown, put top on. Turn oven down to 200° and let simmer for about 40 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add beef and mix well.
Shape into 10 patties.
Brown well on both sides.
Pour off grease.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Cook slowly until steak is done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Mix eggs, sugar, cinnamon, pumpkin, baking soda and flour together.
Pour batter on lined cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine flour, yeast, salt and sugar in mixing bowl and stir. Add vegetable oil and water.
Mix together all ingredients.
Knead by hand 3 minutes.
Shape.
Put into bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in volume.
Punch down; divide into 2 equal pieces and shape into 2 round balls or leave in 1 piece for 16-inch pizza. Let dough rest 4 minutes.
Rol out 12 to 16-inch diameter.
Place on pizza pan; let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sauce and toppings. Place on bottom rack of cold oven.
Turn oven to 500° and bake 17 to 20 minutes.

title: how to cook a country ham
directions: Boil ham 1 hour, covered in water, on top of stove. Put in large turkey bag. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Put 2 cups of water inside bag; tie bag. Slit 3 holes in top of bag. Put in oven at 400° for 1 hour, then turn oven down 200° for about 4 hours. Take out and let cool and bone it. Tie it with string and let cool before slicing.

title: bob hall's microwave scottish chili
directions: Cook meat in microwave until cooked.
Drain and break up in wee bits.
Add everything else.
Mix. Cook on High for 30 minutes.
May be served with elbow noodles.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in 2 cups boiling, salted water.
Add corn and cream.
Add crumbled bacon, chopped onion, pepper and paprika. Blend mixture and serve hot.

title: old fashion chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add beaten eggs, flour and other ingredients.
Bake at 325°.
Take out before brown.

title: date nut bread
directions: Measure warm water into a warm large bowl; sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Add warm milk, sugar, salt and margarine. Stir in 2 cups all-purpose flour; beat with rotary beater until smooth (about 1 minute).
Add 1 cup all-purpose flour; beat with rotary beater until smooth (about 1 minute).
Add 1 cup all-purpose flour; beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until smooth (about 150 strokes).
Stir in whole wheat flour, dates, pecans, cinnamon and enough of the remaining all-purpose flour to make a soft dough.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in freezer.

title: cranberry-pecan muffins
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and add vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups half full.
Combine sugar and nutmeg.
Sprinkle small amount on each muffin.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together the sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix, making sure cream cheese is smooth.
Lay down as a foundation on a cookie sheet.
Pour taco sauce over top.
Next, layer lettuce, cheese and tomatoes on top.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and pecans.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.

title: pear salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot pear juice with Jell-O.
Let that cool.
Mix remaining juice together with cream cheese.
Mash pears and mix together.
Fold in Dream Whip.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
When cool, stuff with meat mixture.
Cover completely with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until done.
Take off cover and spread with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Put back in oven until the cheese melts.

title: j. t. w. quickie chickie
directions: Put chicken in shallow baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Great with rice and salad.

title: chocolate wafer slice
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine. Add sugar, egg and cocoa; boil for one minute. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, walnuts and graham crumbs. Mix well. Press into greased 9x11 inch pan. Chill. Frost with butter icing when cooled.

title: sweet and sour cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill thoroughly before serving.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse lightly with cold water.
Mix all ingredients together (shrimp will break up).
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter.
Add grated cheese, salt and red pepper.
When thoroughly creamed, add flour.
Add Rice Krispies.
Place small ball of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with floured fork tines.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, bean dip, hot pepper sauce, sour cream, scallions and taco seasoning mix with electric mixer, adding one ingredient at a time.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix salt, peppers and onions.
Add hominy, soup and cheese. Melt margarine.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Pour over other mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Recipe is better and chewier if doubled.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, sausage, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard. Layer with bread and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Cook sausage in skillet, stirring frequently, until no longer pink; drain.

title: cornbread(small pan)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 1 tablespoon cooking oil into small frying pan.
Heat; then pour mix into pan (hot oil).
Brown a little.
Then put in oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef jerky (king b style)
directions: Trim off excess fat from meat.
Cut into strips approximately 1/4
inch
thick
and 2 inches wide.
This can be done more easily if
the
meat is partially frozen.
Mix remaining ingredients together
and
marinate
in this sauce overnight. Use a flat pan if available.
Cover with clear wrap.

title: 2 dozen sandwiches
directions: Slice entire pan of rolls to become split buns.
You can do this without removing them from the pan.
Combine all ingredients except the ham and cheese.
Spread both sides of buns with mixture.
Layer ham over tray of rolls.
Top with cheese and top of rolls.
Cover the tray with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake per package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt butter, evaporated milk and caramels.
Pour over first layer.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter on top. Finish baking for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate almond mousse
directions: Melt chocolate and water in pan or on Low in microwave. Watch; it burns rapidly.
Stir until blended and smooth.
Cool slightly.
Combine cooled chocolate, milk, cream and flavorings in mixer bowl.
Mix just until all chocolate is evenly distributed; stir from bottom of bowl.
Chill bowl and contents.
Whip until soft peaks form.
Fold in almonds.
Spoon into shallow pan or crystal goblets.
Freeze until firm.
May be garnished with a bit of sweetened whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings and is super easy to do.
Remove from freezer 40 minutes before serving, depending on room temperature.
Is best when partially frozen and flavor comes through.

title: creamy pasta with mushrooms
directions: Prepare fettuccine as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.
Gradually add skim milk to fat-free mayonnaise and garlic in a small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; blend in Egg Beater.
Toss with fettuccine until well coated.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Serves 8.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Combine hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add beans and seasonings; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: irish tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to slow (325°).
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3) loaf pans. Place 2/3 cup flour in medium size bowl.
Add currants and toss well to coat; set aside.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder onto waxed paper.
Beat together butter, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla in large bowl of electric mixer and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk in 3 or 4 additions, beginning and ending with dry ingredients, mixing after each addition only enough to just combine ingredients.
Fold in currants and all the coating flour.
Spoon batter into prepared pans, dividing equally. Smooth tops.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes or until loaves are lightly browned and springy to the touch and begin to pull away from the sides of the pans.
Cool cakes in pans on rack 15 minutes.
Carefully loosen cakes around edges with thin bladed spatula.
Turn out on racks and cool right side up for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine cheeses, egg, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of pan.
Place shells open side down.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: weight watcher's southwestern white chili
directions: Heat oil in a 3-quart saucepan on high.
Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove the chicken with a slotted spoon, cover and keep warm.
Add onions, beans and spices.
Cook 2 minutes and stir in broth.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in cooked chicken and simmer for 10 minutes. Garnish with Monterey Jack cheese and green onions.
(Counts as 3 proteins, 2 breads, 1 fat and 5 optional calories.)

title: chinese salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables and rinse.
Combine and toss to mix.
Pour vinegar and sweetener or sugar over and mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain the spinach.
Mix rest of ingredients.

Add drained spinach and let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours. Serve the dip in a hollowed out, 1 pound round loaf of hard bread. Use the portion of the middle of the loaf cut into bite size pieces to dip.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pull off mushroom stems.
Wipe with damp towel.
Brush outside mushrooms with melted butter.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese and bacon.
Stuff in caps.
Preheat oven to 370°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in shallow pan or until caps are tender, stuffing light brown.

title: cinnamon maple syrup
directions: Combine the corn syrup, brown sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add the maple flavor, vanilla extract and cinnamon. Pour in a bottle.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook garlic 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Toss with fettucine.
(Garnish if desired with cherry tomatoes and parsley.)

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 2 layers.
Split each layer with thread.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Mix with mixer and put into bowl.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep several days and may be frozen if desired.

title: cinnamon surprise pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time until mixed well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour half of batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread this mixture evenly over batter in pan.
Pour rest of batter in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: savory brown rice
directions: In a saucepan, combine onion and 1/4 cup water.
Cook on medium heat until onion is tender.
Add rice, 2 cups water and soy sauce. Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well. Cover and simmer over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Let rest in covered pan for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes a good side dish to serve with vegetables.

title: chicken something different
directions: Line bottom of greased oblong glass baking dish with layers of dried beef.
Wrap each breast with bacon strips and secure with toothpick.
Place breast in 2 rows of 4 each on top of beef.
Mix together soup and sour cream and pour over chicken, spreading to completely cover.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 250°.

title: orange roughy with vegetables
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
In a large skillet, combine the water, onion slice, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and add fish fillets and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until fillets flake when tested.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, cook mushrooms, pepper, onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in chopped tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce; cook 2 minutes. Transfer vegetables to serving platter.
With slotted spoon, remove fish from cooking liquid and place on vegetables.

title: polynesian shrimp dip
directions: Cut 1-inch thick slice from top of pineapple, leaving green leaves on top. Reserve top. With curved knife, cut out fruit from shell, leaving 1/2-inch wall. Cut fruit into cubes, removing any fibrous core.

title: sausage and green beans
directions: Use deep skillet with lid.
Place bacon grease in skillet.
Let melt and add frozen green beans and onion.
Let fry in skillet while you cut up the sausage in about 1/2-inch pieces.
Add sausage.
Scrub potatoes and quarter.
Add to skillet.
Cover.
Let cook on medium-high 1 hour.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes to prevent burning.
Great served with corn bread.
Serves 5.

title: simply delicious pumpkin cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pumpkin.
Stir until moistened.
(Do not add any other ingredients.)
Batter will be stiff.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve as is or top with Cool Whip, powdered sugar or cream cheese frosting.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in slightly greased casserole dish (10 in.).
Cover with bacon crumbs and sliced stuffed olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and the casserole is hot through.

title: jello whip green salad
directions: Mix jello, water and sugar.
Let set until slightly congealed. Whip congealed gelatin mixture.
Add whipped topping.
Stir in the pineapple and cream cheese that has been broken into small pieces.
Stir in the pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour with milk and sugar. Pour on top of margarine.
Add fruit.
Bake until crust is golden.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and milk; cook until thick.
Add grated cheese.
Place ingredients in layers in dish and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: southern style corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour with corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix eggs, milk and shortening.
Mix with dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a 10-inch skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a boil on low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir and beat until thick. Pour into a greased pan.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: dirt
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, puddings and Cool Whip.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture.
Crush Oreos in a blender.
Into a pot or bucket, alternate cookies and pudding mixture, end with cookies.
Serve with a spade or shovel (child's) and decorate tops with gummy worms and flowers.

title: cinnamon crunchies
directions: Warm skillet on low heat.
Add cereal; stir.
Add cinnamon and sugar, a little at a time.
Stir constantly.
Continue stirring over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in tight container.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together; add remaining ingredients. Pour into flat greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black raspberry and orange salad
directions: Set Jell-O. When cool, add relish, celery and pecans.
Put into Jell-O mold.

title: raisin tea loaf
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and lemon rind.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine lemon extract, vanilla and milk; add alternately with dry ingredients to raisin mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and rind and vanilla. Mix at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended and add one yolk at a time until finished with egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites by hand.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Melt margarine in baking dish. Stir together flour, sugar and milk. Pour mixture in melted margarine. Put pie filling in middle of mixture. Bake 35-40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and curry powder.
Bring to boil.
Drain fruit.
Arrange in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish and pour hot sauce over the fruit.
Garnish with cherries.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: quick manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions; drain. Rinse in cold water; drain and set aside.
Saute ground beef and garlic, stirring to crumble beef, until beef is no longer pink; drain off pan drippings.
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayonnaise to skillet.
Stir well.
Stuff manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Arrange shells in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine spaghetti sauce and oregano. Pour over manicotti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: irish scones
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and butter (stir or cut in butter) until dough resembles coarse meal.
Beat eggs and cream.
Pour egg mixture into dry mixture.
Mix until moistened and add currants and mix.
Drop batter in 3 ounce size rounds onto greased cookie sheet.
Makes 12 to 15 scones.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian sprout sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place 1 cheese slice atop each muffin half.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/3 cup vegetable mixture atop each half.
Add 2 tablespoons of sprouts and 1 teaspoon sunflower seeds.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Beat butter in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar; continue to beat.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternately add flour with salt and milk, then chocolate and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Do not open oven door while baking.
May add nuts and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off liquid.
Combine green beans (liquid too) and soup.
In a large casserole thinly slice potatoes and sprinkle with salt.
Add 1/2 beef, then 1/2 green bean mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese, beating until well blended. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve with purchased ginger snaps.
Yield 7 cups.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together.
Put popcorn, peanuts and candy in large container.
Pour marshmallows and melted butter mixture over popcorn and candy mixture.
Mix well.
Press into tube or Bundt pan, well-greased, with butter.
When set, ease out onto cake plate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Brown meat.
Add onion, garlic, broth, thyme and liquid from mushrooms.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Slice mushrooms and add.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Turn heat off and allow sour cream to heat through.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: candy fudge
directions: Melt cheese, butter and cocoa on low heat. Add remaining ingredients. Stir; put in buttered pan to cool.

title: tacky tourist mango velvet fruit dip
directions: Peel mangos and cut into chunks.
Place fruit in blender until pureed.
Add orange juice concentrate and lime juice.
Whirl until blended.
Great to dip fruit in or serve with fruit kabobs.

title: better than anything chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into prepared pan.
After 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Continue baking until cake is done.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in it about 1-inch apart with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Then pour caramel sauce over cake and especially into holes.
Let cool.
(Can put in refrigerator for 1 hour.)
Top with whipped cream and crushed Heath bars.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: salmon loaf(6 servings)
directions: Free salmon from skin and bones.
Flake salmon.
Combine beaten eggs, lemon juice and rest of ingredients.
Taste and add more salt, if needed.
Form into loaf and place into greased pan. Bake in 350° oven until delicately browned and firm (about 1 hour).

title: cinnamon cuke rings
directions: Peel, core and slice cukes.
Put in solution for 24 hours. Lift rings out of water, wash and drain well.
Do this 3 times. Add the 1 cup vinegar, alum and enough water to cover rings.
Add food coloring.
Heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Lift rings out of solution.
Discard solution.
Make syrup with 6 cups water, sugar, red hot candy, 6 cups vinegar and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cuke rings.
Cover.
Let set overnight.
Drain syrup.
Reheat.
Pour over rings.
Let set overnight again.
Do this for 3 days.
On the third day, heat to boiling.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip meltaways(in honor of single g)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill dough for 10 minutes before making cookies.
Between the making of cookie batches, put dough in the refrigerator until ready to use each time.
Drop cookie dough by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 325°
oven until lightly browned on the bottoms and somewhat firm on the tops (around 10 minutes).

title: stewed mushrooms
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, saute onion in oil.
Add green pepper and sliced mushrooms.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add seasoning, water and parsley.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Make a paste of the flour and cream, then add to mushrooms.
Simmer about 5 more minutes.
Serve on toast or with mashed potatoes.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, 15 to 20 minutes, or until thick.
Remove.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar.
Press into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: mexican pepper steak
directions: Trim steak of all fat, gristle and bone.
Cut across grain into 1-inch wide strips.
Brown steak in oil in a large skillet. Add tomatoes, onions, mushrooms and barbecue sauce to meat.
Cover skillet and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir in green strips.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Roll mixture in cabbage leaves.
Cover and cook in iron frying pan about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Mix in vanilla and pumpkin.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together real good.
Spread on cookies.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar. Will frost two 9-inch layers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix beans, corn, bell pepper and onion. Mix in soup and sour cream.
Blend in grated cheese.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crushed cracker crumbs mixed with 1 stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and baking powder and cut in margarine. Mix until crumbly, then add oatmeal, coconut and walnuts. Press 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of mixture on top of pie filling.
Can use strawberry, blackberry or apricot pie filling. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spinach lasagne rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Add spinach and cook until tender, 4 minutes.
Cool.
Combine spinach, Ricotta, Parmesan, egg and parsley in a large bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of an 8-inch dish.
Put 1 lasagne noodle (dry) on wax paper sheet. Spread 1/3 cup Ricotta mixture over noodle.
Roll up noodle.
Place seam, side down, in dish.
Repeat with all noodles.
Top with 1 cup sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake about 45 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: fudge
directions: Put chocolate bits, pecans, oleo and vanila in large bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar, marshmallows and Pet milk in saucepan and boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly before and after boiling.
Pour over ingredients in bowl and stir until chocolate melts.
Pour into buttered dish and cool.
Cut.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh to maintain color and apples won't turn brown.
mix well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add both cans of soup.
Mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Lay Tater Tots on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over medium heat in large skillet.
Add garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in the Prosciutto and saute 2 minutes more.
Add the cauliflower and cook just until it begins to lose its crispiness, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in flour, then cream.
Blend.
Season with cayenne, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling and immediately remove from heat.
Pour the cauliflower into shallow dish.
Top with the cheese and parsley.
Bake until lightly browned and bubbling, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 portions.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg, beat just until blend.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended.
Baking on ungreased baking sheet 7 to 8 minutes or until just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.

title: 14 karat meat loaf
directions: Place onion in a 1 cup glass measuring cup.
Cover and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: good-n-easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add garlic seasoning.
Add tomato sauce over meat; simmer.
Cook noodles; drain and pour cold water over them. In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce, grated cheese, cottage cheese and top with Parmesan cheese until all used.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter and milk.
Mix together with dry ingredients. Make small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.

title: chocolatetown special cake
directions: Stir together cocoa and boiling water in small bowl until smooth; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch or two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool completely and frost.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar.
Add
egg
and
vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add rhubarb. Mix 1/4 cup sugar and
1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Delicious warm with ice cream or milk.

title: preacher's casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook onion, celery and green peppers in a small amount of olive oil until transparent.
Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/4 of noodles to sprinkle on top. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: Salt chicken and place in baking dish.
Mix onion soup mix and Russian dressing together.
Add orange marmalade.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes until chicken is done and sauce has formed a glaze.

title: e. t.'s salmon patties
directions: In large bowl, combine torn bread slices, salmon, eggs, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Shape into patties.

title: beef brisket
directions: Rub brisket with garlic.
Add salt, pepper and ginger.
Cover with A.1. sauce and ketchup.
Sprinkle allspice on the top.
Place around brisket the onion, carrot and celery.
Add water.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 300° for about 3 hours for 4 pounds of beef.

title: baked cheese fondue
directions: Put layer of cheese and layer of bread in large casserole dish.
Continue layers, ending with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt (pepper and Worcestershire sauce).
Beat until well mixed.
Pour liquid over layers and allow to stand at least 10 hours in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour prior to baking time.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 7 or 8 people.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook 2 minutes.
Drain off excess fat and add celery.
Cool.
Beat eggs and salt slightly.
Add bacon, bean sprouts, parsley, ham, scallions and bouillon and stir well.
Heat oil in skillet hot, but not smoking. Drop in big spoonfuls of egg mixture about 3 inches across. Shape into round cakes before egg sets.
Cook until lightly browned.
Turn and brown underside.
Lift onto paper towel, then serve piping hot.

title: beer batter for vegetables
directions: Mix together flour, salt and beer.
Mix will be firm.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Stir in small amounts of egg whites at a time (to keep batter light).
Dip vegetables into batter and drop into hot oil, one piece at a time.
May store any leftovers for 2 to 3 days.
Can use on fruit fritters.

title: apple pecan cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the apple pie filling brown sugar and cinnamon; stir in the nuts.
Spread half the mixture in the pie crust.
Refrigerate the remaining mixture.
Place the milk and half and half in a medium size bowl; add the instant pie filling mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in the whipped topping.
Spoon mixture over the apple mixture in the pie crust.
Freeze for at least 2 hours before serving.
Remove from the freezer about 10 minutes before serving and garnish with the reserved apple mixture and additional whipped cream topping, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugars and oil in large bowl.
Beat well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in carrots, vanilla, raisins and walnuts.
When well blended, pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for one hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on rack before covering or cutting.

title: spinach salad
directions: Make the salad dressing by mixing oil and sugar in a blender for approximately 5 minutes.
Add dry mustard and salt, blend just a little more.
Add vinegar slowly while the blender in on low.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add sugar and salt; stir in syrup and mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with pecans; refrigerate.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine veggies, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: icebox potisa
directions: Measure flour and sift with sugar and salt.
Cut in the butter as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add sugar in it.
Let it stand until it foams.
Mix together the egg yolks, 1 cup of sour cream and the foaming yeast.
Make a dent in the flour mixture and add the yolks, sour cream and foaming yeast into the flour mixture.
Knead into a smooth dough.
Put the dough into the refrigerator overnight.
The next day, roll out the dough and fill it with nut filling.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix cooked broccoli, cooked rice and cream of mushroom soup and add desired amount of Velveeta cheese. Melt and mix well. Spread in a 3-quart casserole dish. Top with Velveeta and bake at 350° until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: buttery french bread
directions: Slice bread.
In a small bowl, combine butter, paprika and celery seed.
Spread between bread slices and over top.
Wrap bread tightly in foil.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Open the foil and bake 5 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Line a 9 x 9-inch pan
with
enough
foil
to cover and seal the contents.
Butter
the	bottom	foil.
Arrange sliced potatoes in 4 flat parallel rows overlapping each other.
Slip a
couple of rings of onions
between
every
2	or
potato slices. Sprinkle with salt,
pepper
and
garlic.
Dot
with butter. Bring oil over potatoes and seal well.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 50 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Crumble cornflakes over bottom of dish.
Spread cabbage over corn flakes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a pot, bring to boil soup, milk, margarine and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage.
Spread cheese over casserole. Crumble corn flakes over cheese.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy tomato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook until well heated.
Ready to serve.

title: pork in garlic sauce
directions: Pound chops and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in skillet and lightly brown chops on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and saute about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add flour and stir into onion mixture until blended.
Add bouillon and mustard, stirring until mixture is smooth, then add meat.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 30 to 45 minutes.
(Makes 4 servings.)

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, soup mix and eggs.
Put 1/2 of mixture into large oven container and shape into a rectangular loaf.
Be sure to leave space on all sides of loaf.
With fingers form a shallow well lengthwise.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, green pepper and parsley and spoon into the well.
Pat remaining meat mixture on top.
Cover the loaf with tomato juice and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
To complete, add potatoes; submerge into juice surrounding loaf.
Add green salad and a crispy loaf of bread.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine.
While hot add 1 bottle Italian dressing and 1 bottle of salad seasoning.
When cooled add vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours before serving.

title: anne's salsa
directions: Chop onion and pepper and put all ingredients in a blender. Mix with a spoon before turning on blender.
Use the chop setting on the blender for 30 to 45 seconds.
The amount of jalapenos is for your personal taste depending on how hot you like it.
Store in a glass jar in refrigerator.
The longer it stays in the jar the hotter it gets.
Do not store in a plastic bowl.

title: lazy cucumber pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions, bell pepper and salt in a large glass bowl.
Refrigerate for two hours.
(Do not drain.)
Whisk together vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over cucumber mixture and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage, green pepper and onion in skillet; drain.
Put it back in the skillet and stir in egg until cooked.
Roll out bread dough into a rectangle on a floured surface.
Spread sausage mixture on dough and sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Roll into a loaf.
Put on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes.

title: peanut butter doo-doo
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: arabic meat pies
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add parsley, salt and pepper to taste, vinegar and tahini.
Mix well.
Flatten each biscuit with fingers, creating a depressed center.
Place a tablespoon (or less) filling on each biscuit disc.
Spread to within edge of biscuit.
Press several pine nuts into filling.
Bake according to biscuit directions, 400° on ungreased sheet for 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Prepare 12 hours before serving and keep refrigerated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast and 1/4 cup warm water together. Add to remaining ingredients and knead until smooth. Let rise until doubled in size; pinch down and knead again. Make rolls or loaves. Bake rolls 25 minutes and loaves 35 minutes at 375°.

title: betty's three bean salad
directions: Drain and wash beans.
Add next 3 ingredients. Add dressing. Mix with salad and let stand overnight.

title: homemade southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Knead flour, shortening and milk together until tacky.
Roll out; cut with a small cup.
Place in a cast-iron skillet; bake until lightly brown.

title: corn noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add cheese, oleo and sugar; stir well.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet red pepper salad
directions: Place whole peppers on a broiler pan; broil 4 inches from the heat until the skins blister, about 2 to 3 minutes.
With tongs, rotate pepper slightly; broil until all sides are blistered and lightly blackened.
Place pepper in a brown paper bag; close bag and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Peel off the charred skin and discard; remove stem and seeds.
Cut peppers into 1/4 inch wide strips.
In a shallow container, combine the oil, parsley, garlic, oregano and salt; add peppers and toss.
Cover and chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, cut in shortening; add buttermilk and yeast.
Mix until moistened throughout.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Will last 2 weeks in refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: best ever banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese with Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add pudding mix with 3 cups milk and beat until thick.
Add Cool Whip. Layer in large bowl with cookies and bananas.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potato, pineapple, raisins, sugar, vanilla and salt in medium mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 8-inch square pan.
Pour milk and butter evenly over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Can add nuts and marshmallows.

title: fresh orange layer cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients into bowl.
Add the shortening and orange rind.
Measure the orange juice and water or milk into a liquid measuring cup.
Add 2/3 of this liquid to dry ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining liquid and the unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake in two 8 x 1 1/2-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until done.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix with softened margarine and 1 egg.
Press into pan.
Sprinkle chips over mix evenly.
Beat eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour over mix and chips.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over this.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased). Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in pieces and put in a pan to cook, cover in one quart of water, add one teaspoon salt for 40 minutes, on high temperature.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, salt, sugar and hot milk.
Mix well.
Mix egg snow point, add the other ingredient and mix well.
Grease the glass pan and add the mix.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove when done and cover with marshmallows. Place back in oven for 10 more minutes.

title: duffie's baked beans
directions: Mix well
and pour into a baking pan; turn heat low for about 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: basic crustless quiche
directions: Melt the
butter.
Whip
the
eggs until fluffy and add the flour,
baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, melted butter and half
the
Jack
cheese.
At
this	point,	add
any other special ingredients
you wish.
Place the mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Top
with
remaining Jack cheese. Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes; then reduce temperature to 350° and continue to	bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the top is lightly browned. Cool and cut into squares for serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Note: Use a candy thermometer.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Blend orange juice with sour cream. Combine with jello using electric beater until mixture is smooth. Refrigerate.

title: tropical surprise salad
directions: Mix the lemon pudding with the entire can of pineapple; add marshmallows, nuts, coconut, bananas and cherries. Stir well. Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Prepare gelatin using juice of pineapple for part of liquid. Add cream cheese; beat until dissolved.
Pour in molds and chill. Prepare lettuce.
Place sliced pineapple on lettuce and then turn gelatin on pineapple with mayonnaise on top.

title: fat man's pie
directions: Mix together the flour, melted margarine and pecans and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; set aside to cool.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Chop or dice bell peppers.
Place in small pan with water and cook in high heat for 4 minutes. Drain and cool.
Fry sausage and let drain.
Mix cornmeal and flour. Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn.
Beat and mix well.
Stir in onions, peppers and green peppers (bell). Grease a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Warm dish, then mix in half of batter, then top with half of sausage and cheese. Repeat.
Start with batter layer again.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: alma's corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's fresh apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon together.
Put apples in pie shell.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over apples.
Dot with butter.
Put top crust on top of pie.
Cut a circle about an inch around.
Cut slits by sticking a knife in top of crust to let out steam.
Bake pie at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine graham crackers and margarine and form crust in square pan.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and spread over crust.
Add bananas and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with pecans.
Dot with cherries.
Keep in refrigerator.
(Best made the day before serving.)

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; best made a day before for flavor.
Serve with apple slices, chunk pineapple, seedless grapes, etc.

title: corn and green chili casserole
directions: Combine corn, eggs, garlic powder, salt, cornmeal, corn oil and chiles in bowl.
Layer corn mixture and cheese one half at a time in greased 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
May substitute mixture of Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese for all Cheddar.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: garbage bread(always requested at parties)
directions: Puree or mash bananas.
Mix bananas, egg, sugar, oil and orange peel until well blended.
In large bowl, combine flour, poppy seed, baking powder and salt.
Stir banana mixture into flour mixture until evenly blended.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend in a a blender or food processor the carrots, melt and add the butter, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and brown sugar. Beat the eggs together and add to mixture.
Pour in a 6 inch baking dish and cook at 350 for 1 hour or until center of souffle is firm.

title: pork chops (baked)(serves 4)
directions: Brown pork chops in pan (4).
Remove pork chops.
To the same pan add cream of mushroom soup prepared as directions.
Heat to boiling.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add salmon and bread crumbs.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: boneless fried chicken
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs and milk.
If thinner batter desired, add more milk.
Dip chicken in batter and fry in hot oil.
Excellent.
Use up all that leftover turkey.
I've also used this batter to make onion rings.
I don't sift the ingredients, but it still comes out okay.

title: lemon lush
directions: Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix lime Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Add just a little ice. Just before serving, add ginger ale and more ice.

title: bell pepper casserole
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine bell pepper, bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese.
In saucepan, over low heat, stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Gradually add milk to flour and butter mixture. Stir constantly until mixture begins to thicken.
When thickened, stir in 1/2 cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted. Add cheese sauce to bell pepper mixture.
Spoon into well-greased 1-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes to one hour.
Serves 4. This recipe goes well with bake Turkey or Hen.

title: moist and crispy onion chicken
directions: Place onion soup mix and bread crumbs in large plastic bag. Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place one piece at a time in bag and shake until well coated.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix onion, cheese and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nevada's chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Save broth. Saute pepper, onion and celery until tender. Do not brown. Cook spaghetti in broth until tender. Do not drain. Add pepper, onion, celery and cheese. Mix well until cheese melts. Add peas and tomatoes. Add chicken and mix well. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes in large casserole.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir and add more dressing if necessary.

title: fried lumpia rolls
directions: Saute the garlic in olive oil.
Add onion.
Cook until soft. Add chicken breasts.
Brown.
Add string beans, cabbage, carrots and garbanzo beans.
Stir and cook until half done.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cool in a colander,
while allowing liquid to drain out.
When cool, wrap in lumpia wrapper.
Fry in hot oil.
Serve with dipping sauce, mixture of vinegar, crushed garlic and black pepper.

title: bread basket
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and margarine.
Add 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together,
except 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese and the crackers.
Put in casserole dish.
Put cheese and
crackers
on top and bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg white and then roll in crushed corn flakes until well coated on both sides.
Place chicken on baking sheet sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Break cake in pieces and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat milk and pudding until smooth.
Beat in ice cream and pour this mixture over cake.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: festive jello salad
directions: Mix raspberry Jell-O according to directions on package.
Add in cranberry sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Place in refrigerator and let set.
After completely set, evenly spread sour cream over Jell-O mixture and place into refrigerator and let chill.
Next, mix cherry Jell-O according to directions on package; set aside and let cool.
When cooled down, carefully pour onto sour cream.
Place into refrigerator and let completely set.

title: beef roast and gravy
directions: Wash roast well.
Slice roast in half crosswise and sprinkle with salt, pepper and dry soup mix on all surfaces.
Chop up margarine on top of roast.
Pour water over roast and cook overnight in crock-pot.
In the morning, add mushroom soup and let cook until lunch.

title: cucumber sandwiches(servings:  4)
directions: Coarsely grate cucumber and carefully press out excess moisture with paper towels.
Mix all ingredients and spread on thin white bread.
Trim crusts and cut into fourths.

title: reubens
directions: Put corned beef, sauerkraut and French dressing on rye bread. Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spicy chicken and corn
directions: Dice up chicken and cook until brown.
Remove from skillet. Cut up onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add red pepper, black pepper, salt and oregano to green pepper, onion and paprika.
Mix golden corn and stewed tomatoes into pepper and onion.
Add chicken and cooked rice.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: three step cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, poke cake top with holes and spread the condensed milk over the top, filling holes.
Then spread butterscotch topping.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars. Refrigerate.

title: quick brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (chocolate unmelted).
Pour into well greased 8-inch square pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a moderate (350°) oven.
Be careful not to overbake.
Cut into squares and remove from pan while hot.

title: summer punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a ring mold and freeze. Just before serving, in punch bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Float frozen ring.

title: oven fried vegetables
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray. Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick spray. Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika together well. Put the vegetables in a bowl. Drizzle with the salad dressing and roll in the bread crumb mixture. Bake in a 450° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden. Makes 4 servings.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press against sides and bottom of pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake(from the files of charlie mae williams)
directions: Pour water over oats; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy; gradually beat in sugars.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Stir in oats mixture.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixtures; blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove cake from pan.

title: canadian meat pie
directions: Cook meat in water, just enough to cover meat, about 1/2 hour. Use fork, and break up meat so it's smooth. Add spices and bread crumbs. Cook 30 minutes or longer, until water is gone. Cool. Place in pie crust. Place crust on top and make slits. Mix egg and water water; brush on top crust. Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and chop into small pieces.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Toss in onion and broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; stir in cheese, salt and rice.
(Milk may be added if too thick.)
Pour into greased baking dish, top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Place raisins in a large bowl.
Cover with boiling water and set aside for 10 minutes.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl.
Add egg, margarine, vanilla and almond extract to raisins and water.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Grease large bowl, set aside.
Heat milk, water and butter in saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in bowl.
Add heated mixture and egg.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out on board; cover with bowl.
Set 10 minutes. Knead until smooth 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape into ball and put in prepared bowl.
Turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Shape dough into balls.
Place 3 balls to one muffin pan cup.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef, drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, basil, and oregano. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In small bowl, combine cottage cheese and egg.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/3 of cottage cheese mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers ending with Mozzarella on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces. Place in bottom of casserole dish.
In another bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well and pour over chicken. Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.
Bake at 325° until warm.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press half of the mixture into a 9-inch baking pan.
Cover the crumb mixture with the diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla and cook until thick and clear.
Pour this sauce over the rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumb mixture and bake in moderate oven for 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: mexicali dip
directions: Microwave (High) cream cheese, uncovered, in microsafe bowl, 30 to 45 seconds or until soft. Beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream. Stir in onions, picante sauce and olives. Refrigerate until served. For zippier flavor, add 3 or 4 drops of pepper sauce. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal; stir in milk and oil.
Divide dough into 3 equal portions.
Roll each into 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread 1/3 of sausage over dough and top with 1/3 cup cheese.
Roll up jellyroll fashion, beginning with long side; pinch seam and ends to seal.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices; place on ungreased mesh wire racks or baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and cocoa together well. Add other ingredients, blending well. Pour into unbaked, deep dish pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork.
Bake potatoes on a rack at 400° for about 1 hour or until done.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with hot milk until fluffy.
Beat in butter.
Add seasonings.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with bacon and chives and top with cheese.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are piping hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Top with sour cream if desired. Serves 4.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts. Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in nuts.

title: quick hollandaise sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat well.
Warm over very low heat or boiling water.
Serve over cooked broccoli.
Dust with paprika.

title: sausage and egg souffle
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, then cubed bread, salt, cheese, sausage (browned and cooled) and mustard.
Put all together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: talerina
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce and Worcestershire.
Brown ground chuck with sausage.
Add olives and noodles.
Place in large casserole dish that has been coated with Pam.
Add grated cheese.
Heat 30 minutes at 325°.

title: poor man's steak in a skillet
directions: In large bowl, chop onion and pepper.
Add 1 pound ground meat and bread crumbs.
Mix together well.
Make patties and cover both sides with flour.
In large skillet, brown patties slightly on both sides.
Next, cover the patties with mushroom soup.
Add 1 can of water (wash out soup can).
Cook until patties are done and you have a rich gravy (about 30 minutes).
Serve over rice if you like.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
With hands, mix flour, butter, confectioner's sugar until smooth.
Spread thin with fingers in 8-inch square pan (greased).
Bake 25 minutes.
Stir remaining ingredients into beaten eggs.
Spread over top of baked pastry. Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: quick corn sticks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place thinly sliced apples into a pie pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon together. Sprinkle over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, butter, salt, egg and nuts together.
Pour over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: elizabeth clarke's exceptional custard sauce
directions: Place slices of ladyfingers, pound or sponge cake on bottom and sides of deep dish. Sprinkle cake with 2 tablespoons sherry, Port or any fruit flavored liqueur.
Place over cake a round of bananas and fresh or drained cooked fruit of your choice. Fill with a cooked rich custard (box of vanilla will do).
Alternate custard and fruit until deep dish is filled. Top
with freshly whipped heavy cream. Decorate top with cherries and bananas. Enjoy!

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: 300 dollar cake(regular and soft diets)
directions: Mix 6 cups sugar and 6 cups flour in large bowl.

Mix in a saucepan and bring to boil one minute, stirring constantly, 3 cups water, 1 1/2 cups Wesson oil, 3 sticks butter and 3/4 cup cocoa. While the mixture is hot, pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Stir well, then add 1 1/2 cups buttermilk, 6 eggs and 3 teaspoons soda. Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: olie bollen(dutch doughnuts)
directions: Sprinkle yeast and 1/2 teaspoons sugar on milk; stir to dissolve.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt into bowl.
Make a well in the center. Add yeast and eggs; mix just until blended.
Stir in raisins, apple, candied fruit and lemon peel.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil (350°), frying until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yield: approximately 15.

title: swiss oven baked chicken
directions: Cover bottom of a 2-quart bowl with chicken breasts.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Pour can of cream of chicken soup over top. Cover with 1 inch or until bowl is full of Pepperidge Farm bread cubes (not dressing mix).
Pour can of chicken broth over top. Top with grated Swiss cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio salad dessert
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pudding, add nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in cool whip.
Put in a 8x8 pan or dessert dish.
Refrigerate a couple of hours, then serve.
Serves 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil; stir well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut soup(a peanut butter and peanut soup.)
directions: In
medium
saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and
celery
and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and mix until well blended.
Gradually stir in chicken broth, stirring to keep mixture smooth;
simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain. Return
liquid to heat and stir in peanut butter, sherry, lemon juice
and	salt.
Heat
through and serve garnished with chopped peanuts.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jan's lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Mix first three ingredients and pat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna delight
directions: Mix tuna, pickles, onion, mayonnaise and spices.
Toast your bread.
Spread or heap tuna on each slice.
Add 1 slice of tomato on each slice of bread.
Warm broiler to 350° then broil slices until cheese is melted.
Serve while hot, to yourself and a friend, along with a coke or cranberry juice and "no salt pretzels."

title: asparagus
directions: Peel the bottom of asparagus.
Cook 1 minute in pot of water; drain.
Place asparagus in ovenproof pan.
Spread with the melted butter; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 500° oven.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello into saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into dish and refrigerate until jelled. Serve on lettuce wedges.

title: chicken and dumplings for the crew(10 people)
directions: In large pot add 2 gallons water, bouillon cubes (optional), onion powder, celery powder, bay leaves and chicken.
Boil approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken from pot, let cool and debone.
Skim grease off broth.
Return to boil.
Return chicken to pot.
Add livers (optional).
Add parsley and jalapeno peppers (optional).
Mix in soup, stirring well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add noodles; cook approximately 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat, cover with tight fitting lid and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread, crackers or corn bread.
Halve ingredients for 5 people.

title: cheese gobblers
directions: Unroll 1 package crescent rolls (all together) on a cookie sheet.
Mix softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla in mixer until smooth.
Spread on crescent rolls (almost to edge). Roll other package of crescent rolls out on top of cheese mixture. Close up edges by mashing with a fork.
Brush top with egg yolk; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not cut until completely cool.
(I usually put in refrigerator overnight.)
Cut off edges, then cut any way you like.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and sauce
directions: Mix mushroom gravy and sweet and sour sauce.
Put aside.
Brown pork chops.
Place pork chops in large casserole dish.
Cover with sauce mixture.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Eat with mashed potatoes and vegetables.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix and bring to boil.
Cook about 30 minutes or until desired thickness.
Put in sterilized jars, seal and process in hot water canner 10 minutes.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar. Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm and serve. Must be kept in freezer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. With an electric mixer, cream 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add the egg and continue beating to blend well.
Add the molasses. Mix the dry ingredients together in another bowl,
then add to the butter mixture.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Place the remaining sugar in a shallow dish.
Roll tablespoonfuls of the dough into balls, then roll the balls in the sugar to coat.
Place the balls 2 inches apart on the cookie sheets and flatten slightly.
Bake until golden around the edges but soft in the middle, 12-15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before transferring to a rack to cool.

title: baked carrot squares
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with
nonstick
coating
spray.
In
a
medium
size bowl combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and Sweet 'N
Low. In	a
separate
bowl dissolve baking soda in Butter Buds;	add to dry ingredients.
Stir in egg.
Add carrots and raisins.
Mix thoroughly; pour into pan.	Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
