title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: fruit dessert
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, combine sugar, cornstarch and mace. Stir to mix.
Gradually add water; stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar mixture thickens and becomes shiny.
Add orange to mix and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add to the fruit and grapes to the mix and gently stir to coat.
Put in the dish to serve.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta (al dente); cool.
Mix with olive oil to keep shells separated.
Add seafood, broken into small pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Add 1/2 teaspoon curry powder or more to taste.
Blend all ingredients well.
Best when made ahead of time.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Do not use an electric mixer.
Stir together dry cake mix and pie filling.
Stir in optional ingredients if desired.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely at room temperature.
If desired, dust with powdered sugar or top with powdered sugar glaze or cream cheese frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and onion with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Rinse well.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers; let stand overnight.
Next morning, put in freezer containers.
Put in freezer.

title: granma's apple pie
directions: Mix pie crust according to directions on box. Split the amount in half. Roll bottom crust to fit in bottom of pie pan. Add cinnamon into sugar and mix together.
Slice apples real thin. Fill up pie crust with apples.
Add the cinnamon and sugar into pie crust in pan.
Roll out the top crust and put on top of pie. Press down edge of pie all around.
Pinch holes into pie so juice drips out while cooking.
Make sure you put tinfoil at the bottom of the oven. Pie will leak out juice while cooking. Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Work in butter and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bottoms are slightly browned.
Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Chop salmon fine.
Mix flour and butter together. Bring milk to boil, stir in flour, butter, salmon and seasonings; boil 1 minute.
Add crumbs and cool. Form into croquettes, roll in egg (lightly beaten), dip into crumbs and fry.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add lemon rind. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to first mixture, alternating with milk. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Allow to remain in pan 1/2 hour after removing from oven. Apply glaze (1/4 cup sugar and juice of lemon) to hot bread.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add liquids and boil for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Drain beets well.
Add to mixture and let stand for 1/2 hour over very low light.
To reheat, add a piece of butter.

title: garden salad
directions: Place tomatoes, cucumbers and onions (of course Walla Wallas are the best!) into a bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick pie crust for cobbler
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Pour any fruit over top.
Pour 1/2 cup juice or water on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 1 hour.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll out one crust to fit 9-inch pie pan.
Mix the berries, sugar, tapioca and salt together in large bowl.
Pour into prepared shell.
Dot filling with butter.
Roll out remaining crust to form top crust.
Place over filling. Moisten, seal and flute edges; cut slits in top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 30 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: party punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a punch bowl for a refreshingly delicious punch. Does not say how many it serves.

title: toffee
directions: Spread 2/3 of chopped nuts in a 9 x 12-inch area on Teflon cookie sheet.
Melt butter in saucepan (1 or 1 1/2-quart) on medium-high heat.
Add sugars.
Stir while cooking to 300°. (Watch for two or three puffs of smoke that indicate sugar is beginning to scorch.)
Remove from heat and pour over the nuts on the sheet, carefully, to cover as much as possible.
Quickly sprinkle chocolate chips on hot candy to melt.
Spread chocolate. Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: easy and elegant ham
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set juice aside.
Place half of pineapple in an ungreased 5 quart cooker.
Top with ham. Add cherries, remaining pineapple (to top of ham) and reserved pineapple juice.
Spoon marmalade over ham.
Cover and cook on low for 6 - 7 hours or until heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Put nuts in bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: season's greetings punch
directions: In quart measure or medium, stir sugar into reconstituted lemon juice until dissolved.
Place ice cubes in large punch bowl. Pour in reconstituted lemon-sugar mixture and punch.
Slowly add club soda or ginger ale; stir.
Garnish with cherries and orange slices.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Pull meat from bone; chop and put in large casserole dish.
Add Veg-All.
Add soup, mixed with broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, may be longer.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals, using a meat fork and brush with liqueur, if desired.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions, omitting chilling.
Place half of crumbled brownies in bottom of 3-quart trifle dish.
Top with half of mousse, crushed candy bars and whipped topping.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients, ending with whipped topping.
Garnish, if desired.
Chill 8 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In glass bowl, mix sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on high for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanuts with metal spoon and microwave on high 2 1/4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring with metal spoon, and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stirring quickly, add baking soda and pour onto plain cookie sheet and let harden. You must use glass bowl for microwave and metal spoons for stirring--plastic will melt.

title: paris muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 12 muffin cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly mist a 12 cup Bundt pan with cooking oil spray and dust with flour.
Shake out the excess flour.
Set the pan aside.
Place the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, warm water and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Blend with an electric mixer at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips, making sure they are well distributed throughout the batter.
Pour the batter into the pan.
Place pan in oven. Bake for 45-50 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let cool.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding and spread 1/2 over the cake.
Mix 1 can cherry pie filling and drained crushed pineapple and coconut.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over cake and pudding.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip over cake and mixture.
Repeat the layers. Garnish with nuts.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cut up rhubarb in cubes. Add sugar. Let stand overnight or until enough juice to boil. Boil until fruit is cooked, 10 minutes. Add jello; cook until dissolved. Stir well. Put in jars.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and remove bones.
Cut chicken, tortillas and green chilies into strips.
Mix soups, milk and onion.

Butter a 2-quart casserole and layer 1/3 of all ingredients in this order: tortillas, chicken, peppers and soup mixture, until all are used. Cover with cheese and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours (important).
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour or until bubbly and completely hot.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Beat the cheese and add the chopped ingredients.
Blend well. Form into a ball and chill.
(May roll in chopped nuts.)
Prepare a day in advance.
Serve with crackers.

title: pistachio saladwatergate salad
directions: Prepare pistachio pudding as directed on box; let set up.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and cool whip; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve and enjoy.
Note:
I think it makes a great dessert.

title: grandma's hard potato dumplings
directions: Place riced potatoes in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 of the flour. Sprinkle in salt.
Add remaining flour slowly until dough is crumbly and looks like pie crust.
Pack mixture into balls about the size of snowballs.
Place in boiling water (use large kettle). Bring back to boil. Boil for 20 minutes. Good served with pork and sauerkraut.

title: orange slush
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and place in freezer for at least 24 hours.
Before serving, remove from freezer, and allow to partially thaw, about 30 minutes, at room temperature
Stir and serve, or you can pour Sprite or other carbonated drink over slush and serve.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Add onion, pepper and cheese.
Stir in meat.
Pour into pie crust.
Cook (bake) 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half. Scoop out inside and reserve shells. Beat potatoes and cheese until creamy. Gradually beat in milk. Stir in onion, salt and pepper. Spoon into shells.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a dish at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: zucchini and sausage italiano
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown the sausage; add green pepper and onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender and mixture is slightly thickened. Serves 4 to 6.
May be reheated.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Then pour the whole can of fruit in; removing the grapes.
Beat eggs and add to mix.
Pour in a well-greased pan.
Place 1/2 c. brown sugar and 1/2 c. chopped nuts on the batter before putting in oven.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in casserole dish.
Mix the next 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Add crushed crackers on top; pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. (Suitable for freezing.)

title: st. paddy's float
directions: Mix juice and syrup; add sherbet.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet and let soften.
Stir.
Add lime slices.

title: apple nut dip
directions: Beat sour cream, cream cheese and cinnamon in medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: toffee bars
directions: You will also need a jelly roll pan.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place chicken.
Top with mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine garlic, oregano, pepper and tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 50 minutes, adding sherry for last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Serves 6.

title: bean bread
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients and add milk and eggs.
Stir in beans and pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: freezer beans
directions: Cook 10 minutes in 10 pound pressure cooker.

title: low calorie sherbet
directions: Scoop
out
cantaloupe pulp.
Cut into chunks.
Puree in blender.
Stir
in lemon juice.
Mix together sugar and buttermilk,
cantaloupe
puree and whipping cream.
Pour into 2 quart ice cream
freezer.
Use approximately 3 parts crushed ice to 1 part rock
salt.
When
sherbet
is ready, re-pack in ice cream freezer for 2 hours.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; fold into creamed mixture.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch spring-form pan.
Combine pecans, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Sprinkle three-fourths of pecan mixture over batter in pan.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining pecan mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from sides of pan; let cool completely.
Makes 1 (10-inch) coffee cake.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and water in bowl; add sugar and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead on waxed paper.
Make into shapes.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes on a greased cookie sheet. Makes about 36.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: In skillet, heat butter very hot.
Add cole slaw mixture.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, tossing vigorously, until almost tender.
Mix in seasonings, stirring vigorously.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until it is as tender as desired.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut fruit cake
directions: Mix well, beating after each addition.
Grease and line bottom of angel food pan.
Use 2 thick pieces of brown paper.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Keeps moist for a long time.

title: fall salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, celery, nuts and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot.
Put on stove and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix it to get all ingredients through.
Makes 4 to 6 pints.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Chop onion and pepper finely; saute in butter until tender. Boil noodles.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for a few minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Top with chocolate frosting.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Blend egg and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Slowly brown meat in hot oil, turning once. Cover and cook over low heat 45 to 60 minutes until tender.
Season.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fit pie crust over deep dish pie pan or casserole dish.
Mix together the cooked vegetables, chicken and gravy.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pie crust and cut slits. Bake 45 minutes or until browned and bubbly.

title: hearty chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cut beans diagonally into thirds.

Toss with lemon juice and steam until tender. Combine tomatoes, onion, carrots, celery and pepper in stock pot with basic chicken broth (8 cups) and slowly bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours or until vegetables are tender. Add beans and cabbage. Simmer 15 minutes. Add chicken and rice or pasta.
Heat.
Sprinkle with parsley. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: quick muffins
directions: Mix and fill a dozen muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: quasida
directions: Spread 1/8 of the refried beans and cheese onto each tortilla. Add hot sauce to taste.
Then fold tortilla and brown in a little oil.
Serve with salad and chips. Serves 4.

title: ham and cheese egg cups
directions: Spread bread with margairne and press, spread side down, into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in skillet and add eggs, ham and onions.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs are almost set.
Add cheese; continue cooking until cheese melts and eggs are done.
Fill toast cups.

title: chicken tikka
directions: Skin and bone the chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix all other ingredients, in a blender if you wish, until smooth. Put the chicken in a shallow pan and pour the mixture of spices over the top.
Marinate, covered, in a cool place (refrigerator) for no less than 2 hours, the longer the better.
Place the chicken on skewers and cook over grill or under the broiler until cooked through.
Enjoy!

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine and add to sugar and flour.
Add eggs, buttermilk and lemon extract.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and set firm.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk, chocolate chips and sugar to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in margarine and vanilla. Serve warm or cold over ice cream. Store in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: grilled marinated mushrooms(serves 8)
directions: In a glass or ceramic bowl, mix together vinegar, oil, garlic, parsley, oregano, sage, salt, pepper flakes and onion slices. Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel.
Toss mushrooms with marinade.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours, tossing mushrooms occasionally.

title: easy no cook, no seal sweet pickles
directions: Drain and rinse the sour pickles.
Slice pickles and pour sugar over them.
Let stand 24 hours, then turn the jar upside down and repeat the process until all the sugar has dissolved.
The sugar will make a syrup.
Pickles can be eaten after 24 hours, but they are best when pickles have sat in syrup for 5 days.

title: liver casserole
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain on paper.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until soft; remove.
Put flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake liver in bag until well covered with flour.
Brown liver in bacon drippings.
Place liver in casserole.
Add onions and bacon.
Put small amount hot water into drippings; stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions and cook until soft in the melted butter (approximately 45 minutes on low heat).
Add Worcestershire sauce and beef consomme.
Simmer on low about 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Layer in crock-pot the chicken parts.
Season each layer with garlic, basil and sauce.
Spread soup (undiluted) over top layer of chicken.
Cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: betty's brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 10 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour kielbasi
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and catsup in blender.
Cut kielbasi into 1/2-inch slices and put in crock-pot.
Pour catsup mixture over and stir.
Simmer several hours.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook garlic and onion until soft in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown ground beef and drain off the fat.
Add ground beef, seasonings, tomato paste and hot water to garlic and onions.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Run until smooth.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 1 cup water, egg yolks, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Heat other cup of water and oleo until oleo melts.
Add to first mixture.
Heat over low flame until thick.
Pour into pie shell; put meringue on and brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn to make about 12 cups.
Place in a large bowl; remove imperfect kernels and sprinkle with salt.
Place butter, molasses and sugar in a saucepan and stir over low heat only long enough for sugar to dissolve.
Simmer until syrup cracks against side of glass when tested in cold water.
Pour over corn.
Add peanuts, if desired, and form into balls with fingers.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 1 stack Ritz crackers (crushed) mixed with 1 stick melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Pour a layer of macaroni into a well-buttered casserole dish.
Cover with half of cheese, salt and pepper; pour half of milk mixture over this.
Repeat next layer same as before.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sesame flank steak
directions: In a 8 to 10-inch heavy frying pan, stir sesame seed over low heat until golden, 2 to 3 minutes.
Crush in a mortar and pestle or food processor.
In a bowl, mix onion, soy sauce, oil, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger, garlic, mustard, Worcestershire and sesame seed.
Place steak in a 9 x 13-inch dish and pour sesame mixture over top.
Cover and chill, turning occasionally, at least 4 hours or overnight.
Cook steak over hot coals, turning once to your liking, 5 to 6 minutes a side for medium-rare.
Cut across the grain in thin slices to serve.
Serves 4.

title: southern peach cobbler supreme
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peaches to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and blend in almond extract and butter.
Roll out 1/2 of pastry to a thickness of 1/8-inch on a flat floured board.
Cut to fit a 2-quart shallow casserole.
Spoon half of the peaches into lightly buttered casserole and top with cut pastry.
Bake at 475° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon remaining peaches over baked pastry. Roll out remaining pastry and cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice over peaches.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings (maybe).

title: kasey's favorite meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except Parmesan.
Lightly pack meat into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter over high heat about 3 minutes. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in crab, shrimp, nutmeg and seasonings.
Stuff each cap with a little of the seafood mixture. Arrange on a large baking sheet.
Place under preheated broiler until bubbling.
Garnish with strips of lemon peel and sprig of mint.

title: old fashioned dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and form into a ball.
Roll dough 1/16 inch thickness, cut into 5x1 inch strips.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cover and cook 15 minutes until dumplings are tender.
May add 1 or 2 tbsp. butter and stir to thicken.
Add cooked chicken.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a large sealable bowl (not metal), layer above ingredients, in order of appearance, up to mayonnaise.
Combine sugar with mayonnaise and spread over salad, sealing edges.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise and then bacon.
Sometimes I also sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the bacon.
Let salad sit in refrigerator at least overnight.
Toss right before serving.

title: peanut butter penuche
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of 8-inch square pan.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt.

title: crunchy cinnamon pecans
directions: Melt butter in a microwave oven on High for 25 seconds. Remove butter from microwave and mix in sugars and cinnamon. Add the pecans and toss until well coated. Spread pecans on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool on wax paper. Makes four 1/2-cup servings.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients to moisten. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Dough will be thick.

title: strawberry crunch salad or dessert
directions: Mix together in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice dough about 1/8-inch thick; place in overlapping form on a 10-inch pizza pan.
Press dough together with fingers to form crust.
Bake for 10 minutes; remove from oven and leave oven on.
Combine yogurt, eggs, flour and lemon peel in small bowl; mix well.
Spread yogurt mixture onto crust.
Return to oven; bake for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Arrange fruit in decorative pattern over filling.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in small pan.
Add water.
Stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is thick; remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Brush glaze over fruit.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Heat
corn syrup and half and half over direct high heat. Lower heat and stir in chocolate.
Heat and stir constantly until chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Yields 1 1/2 cups. Store unused portion in refrigerator.
Dip in the fresh fruits of the season.

title: crumb crust
directions: Turn on oven; set at 375°.
Butter the pie plate.
Soften the butter with a fork.
Crush the crackers or cookies with rolling pin.
Add sugar and softened butter.
Mix well.
Press into pie plate firmly and evenly on the bottom and sides.
Bake the crust for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool before using.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients, then remove from burner.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool to set, then ready to eat.

title: corn nut treat(for birds)
directions: Mix peanut butter and shortening well.
Add cornmeal, a little bit at a time, to get consistency of toothpaste.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a platter.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer on bean dip.
Sprinkle onion, tomatoes, olives and end with layer of cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips or other chips.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: In 8 x 8-inch baking dish, melt margarine.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour over margarine.
Then add fruit over the batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the top and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Pre- Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine crisco, lt brown sugar, milk, and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt, and soda. Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in Chocolate chips.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and butter until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to mixture and mix well.
Roll into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down cookies with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sweet and easy pickles
directions: Boil the vinegar, cinnamon stick, sugar and pickling spice for 3 minutes, then pour into a drained 1 quart jar of hamburger dill slices.
When cool, they are ready to eat.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: In a large pan, blend first 4 ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt. Stir in 10 cups of water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.
Have apples already peeled, cored and sliced.
Pack apple slices into hot fruit jars, leaving 1-inch headspace at top.
Pour bubbly sauce over apples, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes for pints and 20 minutes for quarts.
Yield: 6 to 8 quarts or 12 to 14 pints.

title: milk shake
directions: When
the
younger set wants a milk shake, beat the egg; add peaches,
orange
juice
and milk and mix well.
This will make enough for two small-fry appetites.

title: cream cheese and mushroom enchiladas
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, honey, 1 teaspoon chili powder and remaining spices. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes, until thick, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.

title: cherokee bean bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in milk, eggs, bean juice and beans. Pour into greased pan and bake about 20 minutes at 450°.
Cut and serve.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and let thicken slightly.
Add bananas, oranges and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: pancake layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Spoon about 1/2 cup in round pans and bake until golden.
Makes about 12 layers.
Cool before icing.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bone cooked chicken and put in 12 x 15-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Mix flour, pepper, salt and baking powder.
Add to melted margarine.
Add milk and slowly pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: whipped shortbread cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt in bowl and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine butter, granulated and brown sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts. Drop by well-rounded half teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: zucchine ripiene(stuffed italian squash)
directions: Wash zucchini and scoop out flesh, leaving just enough to keep shell firm.
(This is such a popular dish in Italy that there is a special zucchini corer, much like an elongated apple corer.)
Mix ingredients for filling and stuff the hollowed zucchini.
Put some olive oil and chopped onion in low casserole or baking dish and cook over flame until onion is golden.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into mixing bowl. Stir in caraway seed.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until like coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins.
Combine butter, milk, egg and baking soda and stir into flour mixture until just moistened.

title: tasty dessert
directions: Bring the tapioca mix, Jell-O and water to a boil and boil one minute.
Cool.
Fold in the drained Mandarin oranges and the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in a pan.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir and service with tortilla chips.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Coat chops with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in 2 tablespoons of shortening in pan.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soup, ginger, rosemary, sour cream and water.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle with half the onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and continue baking 10 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and pattie out.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: summer pineapple dip
directions: Toast coconut in butter in frypan or in oven; stir often.
Dip pineapple in sour cream, then roll in coconut.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Dice and saute onion.
Crush chips. Melt in double boiler both cans soup, cheese and tomatoes.
In casserole, layer chicken, onions, chips and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard boiled eggs in half.
Put yolks in a bowl and mash well.
Add the rest of the ingredients,
and mix well.
Fill egg halves with yolk mixture, and sprinkle with paprika (If desired). Eggs take about 15 -20 minutes to boil.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish:
beans, soup, salt, pepper, onion rings, beans, soup, salt, pepper and onion rings.
Cook in oven until it is hot all the way through, around 20 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator relish
directions: Combine
pineapple,
cilantro,	red
pepper
and purple onion in a glass bowl, tossing well.
Combine sugar, vinegar, lime
rind and salt; stir well.
Pour over pineapple mixture. Cover and chill
hours.
Serve relish with grilled pork or chicken, using a slotted spoon.
Store relish in refrigerator. Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Put milk, sugar, salt and lemon peel in saucepan.
Stir over low
heat until sugar dissolves and then bring to a boil.

title: one dish goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck in electric skillet; drain.
Sprinkle chopped onion and pepper, garlic powder, salt, pepper, hot sauce, celery and mushrooms together.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and about 1/2 cup water.
Add macaroni shells and frozen corn. Simmer at low to medium until macaroni shells are done.
Keep adding spices until tastes good.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In large resealable plastic bag, combine 2 Tbsp. Oil, 2 Tbsp. Lemon Juice, and Seasonings. Add Chicken. Seal and turn to coat; refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen banana split
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream sugar and sour cream.
Add rest; add bananas last.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Cover and freeze overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: peanut butter syrup
directions: Stir together.
This syrup does not need to be refrigerated.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer until thickened.
Lightly grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Evenly spread beans on bottom.
Sprinkle with lettuce and onions.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and garnish with tortilla chips.
Serve with chopped tomato, olives, sour cream and taco sauce in separate serving dishes.

title: sunshine gelatin(diabetic)
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup orange juice.
Bring remaining orange juice to a boil.
Mix juice with gelatin mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Add grated carrots and pineapple in its juice; stir well.
Pour into mold; refrigerate until firm.

title: gooey cheesecake
directions: Mix well.
Spread dough in bottom and push 1/2-inch up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: butter frosting
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, butter (Crisco), vanilla and salt.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately, blending until smooth and creamy.
Fills and frosts 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers or 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 475°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix butter and vanilla wafers for crust and bake for 5 to 10 minutes. Beat the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over cooled crust. Sprinkle pecans over mixture. Add Cool Whip. Add pie filling.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini in bottom of 9 x 9 inch or 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 inch baking dish.
Combine carrots and onions and layer over zucchini. Add a layer of stuffing.
Combine soup, sour cream and melted butter and pour over stuffing.
Next add chicken.
If desired, soup mixture can be poured over stuffing and chicken but add 1 cup of additional stuffing to the top and drizzle with 3 Tbsp. of additional melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to box directions (no salt in water).
Mix noodles and cheese together and place in bottom of casserole dish. Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Mix with Ragu sauce and pour on top of noodles. Top with grated Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream fruit dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, preserves and cinnamon.
Chill up to twenty-four hours.
Cut up large pieces of fruit.
Serve with fruit.
Makes one cup (eight servings).

title: oatmeal pancakes(pancakes with "person"ality!)
directions: Beat all ingredients in a medium bowl with a hand beater until smooth.
(For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons of additional milk.)
Grease a heated griddle or pan with shortening or cooking spray.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the hot griddle.
Cook until pancakes are puffed and dry around the edges.
Turn and cook other sides until golden brown. Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together pineapple, pie filling and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple berry pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine cranberries, 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and water.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes while stirring.
Cool 15 minutes.
Prepare pie crust.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine sugar, baking soda and cream.
Cook until the mixture forms a soft ball in cold water (238°).
Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy; add unbeaten egg whites and beat until thick enough to spread onto the cake.

title: old-fashioned corn pudding
directions: Mix everything in bowl (don't bother to separate eggs). Grease casserole	with
butter and pour in mixture.
Place in pie pan with
a
cup of water in it.
Put in 375° oven.
Bake for 1 hour or until it is set in the middle and brown.
Remove from the oven and put a lid on it.
Let stand on stove for 10 to 15 minutes or it will be watery.

title: turkey vegetable pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cook onion, celery in margarine until tender.
Add soups and milk. Stir until smooth.

title: crabmeat florentine
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Place in casserole dish.
Spread crabmeat on top.
Pour Cheese Sauce on top.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
You will be serving from this dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Top with sliced olives if desired.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bread chicken with crumbs; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine; stir in flour. Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cook 2 additional minutes. Add cheese and cook until melted. Add mustard; stir in.

title: peel away bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water and 4 tablespoons butter until hot to touch (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry mixture.
Stir in egg and only enough reserved flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 4 minutes, on a lightly floured surface. Cover; let rise 10 minutes.
Roll into 12-inch square on a lightly floured surface.
Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Cut in 25 squares.
Overlap squares, butter side down, in a greased 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Cover; let rise until doubled in size (about 10 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: raspberry delights
directions: Combine flour, salt, 1 teaspoon sugar and baking powder. Blend in butter. Add egg yolk and milk.
Pat into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Spread with jam.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups sugar, vanilla and melted butter. Add coconut. Spoon over jam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Store airtight. Can be frozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all in the blender until smooth.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Omit baking powder and salt with self-rising flour.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Melt butter on bottom of large pot; add chopped onion, then shredded cabbage.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water and pour over top; add caraway seed.
Put on stove, covered, and cook about 1 hour or more, stirring every 15 minutes until tender.
Add more water if it gets too dry.

title: train wreck mexican dinner
directions: Simmer until thickened.
Serve over taco or tortilla chips. Top with any or all of the following:
shredded lettuce, green peppers, tomato sections, grated cheese, olives and sour cream.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Saute ground beef with onion, garlic, parsley and oregano until meat is browned.
Add rice and saute until translucent.
Add 1/2 tomato paste and 1 cup water and simmer 5 minutes or until liquid is almost absorbed.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cut caps off peppers and remove white membrane.
Reserve caps.
Spoon meat mixture loosely into pepper cavities.
Mix remaining tomato paste with 2 cups water and pour over peppers and into pan.
Cover peppers with caps.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer or until peppers are tender, basting frequently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roast pork with cabbage and carrots
directions: Place pork tenderloin on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Insert a meat thermometer.
Roast in a 325° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour or until thermometer registers 170°.

title: linda's tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients; stir and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: ham and potato scallop for microwave
directions: Pour milk into 2-cup glass measure and cook 2 minutes; set aside.
Put butter in 2-cup measure and cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Briskly stir hot milk, prepared mustard, salt and pepper into butter; set aside.

title: bishops cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add banana and beat again at medium for 2 minutes.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla, beat 2 minutes. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Sprinkle top of each layer with coconut.
Bake in preheated 375 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, them remove and cool, coconut side up on racks.

title: teachers perk coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan with butter.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix the brown sugar with the pudding and sprinkle over the rolls.
Cover and leave on counter overnight. In the morning, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage strata(breakfast dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim bread and place in bottom of a 10 x 4-inch greased casserole.
Brown sausage and drain off grease. Add dry mustard to browned sausage.
Spoon over bread and sprinkle cheese on top of this.
Combine eggs, milk, half and half, salt and Worcestershire; pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can be made in advance.

title: cold linguini salad
directions: Break linguini into thirds.
Boil until done, drain and cool. Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: mexican tostados
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine beef, half the onion and garlic in a frying pan and brown.
Remove fat.
Add tomato paste and seasonings; simmer 20 minutes.
Bake tortillas 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp.
Keep warm.
To serve, place tortillas on individual plates, 2 to 3 per person.
Pass bowls of meat, beans, onions, lettuce, tomato, cheese and salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven baked hash browns
directions: Combine hash browns, soup, sour cream, butter, onion salt & pepper in a large casserole dish. Mix well. Sprinkle cheese over top of dish. Crush corn flakes and sprinkle over the top of the cheese. Cover. Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: pork chops and cabbage
directions: Brown chops in oil in a large skillet. Remove and reserve. Add cabbage and onion to skillet, stirring until cabbage wilts slightly. Combine 3/4 cup apple juice and instant broth; pour into skillet. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt. Sprinkle with caraway. Arrange chops on cabbage; add remaining salt and pepper. Cover with lid and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove chops and cabbage to platter. Whisk remaining 1/4 cup apple juice and cornstarch in bowl. Stir into juice in skillet. Cook until thickened; boil 1 minute.
Pour over chops and cabbage.
Serve.
Enjoy!

title: beans and bacon
directions: Wash, string and break beans.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in water until tender.
Meanwhile, fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion, vinegar, water, sugar, salt, m.s.g. and pepper to bacon and drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Drain cooked beans.
Pour bacon mixture over beans and toss lightly together.
Yield:
4 servings.
Preparation time: 30 minutes; cook time:
20 minutes.

title: crab fondue
directions: Cream cheese and milk in double boiler. Add crab and serve warm with cubes of sour French bread and skewers.
